114 class HexagonCCState : public CCState {
115 unsigned NumNamedVarArgParams = 0;
116
117 public:
118 HexagonCCState(CallingConv::ID CC, bool IsVarArg, MachineFunction &MF,
119 SmallVectorImpl<CCValAssign> &locs, LLVMContext &C,
120 unsigned NumNamedArgs)
121 : CCState(CC, IsVarArg, MF, locs, C),
122 NumNamedVarArgParams(NumNamedArgs) {}
123 unsigned getNumNamedVarArgParams() const { return NumNamedVarArgParams; }
124 };

129// Implement calling convention for Hexagon.
130
131static bool CC_SkipOdd(unsigned &ValNo, MVT &ValVT, MVT &LocVT,
132 CCValAssign::LocInfo &LocInfo,
133 ISD::ArgFlagsTy &ArgFlags, CCState &State) {
134 static const MCPhysReg ArgRegs[] = {
135 Hexagon::R0, Hexagon::R1, Hexagon::R2,
136 Hexagon::R3, Hexagon::R4, Hexagon::R5
137 };
138 const unsigned NumArgRegs = array_lengthof(ArgRegs);
139 unsigned RegNum = State.getFirstUnallocated(ArgRegs);
140
141 // RegNum is an index into ArgRegs: skip a register if RegNum is odd.
142 if (RegNum != NumArgRegs && RegNum % 2 == 1)
143 State.AllocateReg(ArgRegs[RegNum]);
144
145 // Always return false here, as this function only makes sure that the first
146 // unallocated register has an even register number and does not actually
147 // allocate a register for the current argument.
148 return false;
149}

160/// CreateCopyOfByValArgument - Make a copy of an aggregate at address specified
161/// by "Src" to address "Dst" of size "Size". Alignment information is
162/// specified by the specific parameter attribute. The copy will be passed as
163/// a byval function parameter. Sometimes what we are copying is the end of a
164/// larger object, the part that does not fit in registers.
165static SDValue CreateCopyOfByValArgument(SDValue Src, SDValue Dst,
166 SDValue Chain, ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags,
167 SelectionDAG &DAG, const SDLoc &dl) {
168 SDValue SizeNode = DAG.getConstant(Flags.getByValSize(), dl, MVT::i32);
169 return DAG.getMemcpy(Chain, dl, Dst, Src, SizeNode, Flags.getByValAlign(),
170 /*isVolatile=*/false, /*AlwaysInline=*/false,
171 /*isTailCall=*/false,
172 /*MustPreserveCheriCapabilities=*/false,
173 MachinePointerInfo(), MachinePointerInfo());
174}

176bool
177HexagonTargetLowering::CanLowerReturn(
178 CallingConv::ID CallConv, MachineFunction &MF, bool IsVarArg,
179 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs,
180 LLVMContext &Context) const {
181 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
182 CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, RVLocs, Context);
183
184 if (MF.getSubtarget<HexagonSubtarget>().useHVXOps())
185 return CCInfo.CheckReturn(Outs, RetCC_Hexagon_HVX);
186 return CCInfo.CheckReturn(Outs, RetCC_Hexagon);
187}

189// LowerReturn - Lower ISD::RET. If a struct is larger than 8 bytes and is
190// passed by value, the function prototype is modified to return void and
191// the value is stored in memory pointed by a pointer passed by caller.
192SDValue
193HexagonTargetLowering::LowerReturn(SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv,
194 bool IsVarArg,
195 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs,
196 const SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals,
197 const SDLoc &dl, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
198 // CCValAssign - represent the assignment of the return value to locations.
199 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
200
201 // CCState - Info about the registers and stack slot.
202 CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), RVLocs,
203 *DAG.getContext());
204
205 // Analyze return values of ISD::RET
206 if (Subtarget.useHVXOps())
207 CCInfo.AnalyzeReturn(Outs, RetCC_Hexagon_HVX);
208 else
209 CCInfo.AnalyzeReturn(Outs, RetCC_Hexagon);
210
211 SDValue Flag;
212 SmallVector<SDValue, 4> RetOps(1, Chain);
213
214 // Copy the result values into the output registers.
215 for (unsigned i = 0; i != RVLocs.size(); ++i) {
216 CCValAssign &VA = RVLocs[i];
217
218 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, dl, VA.getLocReg(), OutVals[i], Flag);
219
220 // Guarantee that all emitted copies are stuck together with flags.
221 Flag = Chain.getValue(1);
222 RetOps.push_back(DAG.getRegister(VA.getLocReg(), VA.getLocVT()));
223 }
224
225 RetOps[0] = Chain; // Update chain.
226
227 // Add the flag if we have it.
228 if (Flag.getNode())
229 RetOps.push_back(Flag);
230
231 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::RET_FLAG, dl, MVT::Other, RetOps);
232}

234bool HexagonTargetLowering::mayBeEmittedAsTailCall(const CallInst *CI) const {
235 // If either no tail call or told not to tail call at all, don't.
236 auto Attr =
237 CI->getParent()->getParent()->getFnAttribute("disable-tail-calls");
238 if (!CI->isTailCall() || Attr.getValueAsString() == "true")
239 return false;
240
241 return true;
242}

244unsigned HexagonTargetLowering::getRegisterByName(const char* RegName, EVT VT,
245 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
246 // Just support r19, the linux kernel uses it.
247 unsigned Reg = StringSwitch<unsigned>(RegName)
248 .Case("r19", Hexagon::R19)
249 .Default(0);
250 if (Reg)
251 return Reg;
252
253 report_fatal_error("Invalid register name global variable");
254}

256/// LowerCallResult - Lower the result values of an ISD::CALL into the
257/// appropriate copies out of appropriate physical registers. This assumes that
258/// Chain/Glue are the input chain/glue to use, and that TheCall is the call
259/// being lowered. Returns a SDNode with the same number of values as the
260/// ISD::CALL.
261SDValue HexagonTargetLowering::LowerCallResult(
262 SDValue Chain, SDValue Glue, CallingConv::ID CallConv, bool IsVarArg,
263 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, const SDLoc &dl,
264 SelectionDAG &DAG, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals,
265 const SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals, SDValue Callee) const {
266 // Assign locations to each value returned by this call.
267 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> RVLocs;
268
269 CCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, DAG.getMachineFunction(), RVLocs,
270 *DAG.getContext());
271
272 if (Subtarget.useHVXOps())
273 CCInfo.AnalyzeCallResult(Ins, RetCC_Hexagon_HVX);
274 else
275 CCInfo.AnalyzeCallResult(Ins, RetCC_Hexagon);
276
277 // Copy all of the result registers out of their specified physreg.
278 for (unsigned i = 0; i != RVLocs.size(); ++i) {
279 SDValue RetVal;
280 if (RVLocs[i].getValVT() == MVT::i1) {
281 // Return values of type MVT::i1 require special handling. The reason
282 // is that MVT::i1 is associated with the PredRegs register class, but
283 // values of that type are still returned in R0. Generate an explicit
284 // copy into a predicate register from R0, and treat the value of the
285 // predicate register as the call result.
286 auto &MRI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getRegInfo();
287 SDValue FR0 = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, dl, RVLocs[i].getLocReg(),
288 MVT::i32, Glue);
289 // FR0 = (Value, Chain, Glue)
290 unsigned PredR = MRI.createVirtualRegister(&Hexagon::PredRegsRegClass);
291 SDValue TPR = DAG.getCopyToReg(FR0.getValue(1), dl, PredR,
292 FR0.getValue(0), FR0.getValue(2));
293 // TPR = (Chain, Glue)
294 // Don't glue this CopyFromReg, because it copies from a virtual
295 // register. If it is glued to the call, InstrEmitter will add it
296 // as an implicit def to the call (EmitMachineNode).
297 RetVal = DAG.getCopyFromReg(TPR.getValue(0), dl, PredR, MVT::i1);
298 Glue = TPR.getValue(1);
299 Chain = TPR.getValue(0);
300 } else {
301 RetVal = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, dl, RVLocs[i].getLocReg(),
302 RVLocs[i].getValVT(), Glue);
303 Glue = RetVal.getValue(2);
304 Chain = RetVal.getValue(1);
305 }
306 InVals.push_back(RetVal.getValue(0));
307 }
308
309 return Chain;
310}

312/// LowerCall - Functions arguments are copied from virtual regs to
313/// (physical regs)/(stack frame), CALLSEQ_START and CALLSEQ_END are emitted.
314SDValue
315HexagonTargetLowering::LowerCall(TargetLowering::CallLoweringInfo &CLI,
316 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
317 SelectionDAG &DAG = CLI.DAG;
318 SDLoc &dl = CLI.DL;
319 SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs = CLI.Outs;
320 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals = CLI.OutVals;
321 SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins = CLI.Ins;
322 SDValue Chain = CLI.Chain;
323 SDValue Callee = CLI.Callee;
324 CallingConv::ID CallConv = CLI.CallConv;
325 bool IsVarArg = CLI.IsVarArg;
326 bool DoesNotReturn = CLI.DoesNotReturn;
327
328 bool IsStructRet = Outs.empty() ? false : Outs[0].Flags.isSRet();
329 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
330 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
331 auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(MF.getDataLayout());
332
333 unsigned NumParams = CLI.CS.getInstruction()
334 ? CLI.CS.getFunctionType()->getNumParams()
335 : 0;
336 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *GAN = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee))
337 Callee = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GAN->getGlobal(), dl, MVT::i32);
338
339 // Analyze operands of the call, assigning locations to each operand.
340 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
341 HexagonCCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, ArgLocs, *DAG.getContext(),
342 NumParams);
343
344 if (Subtarget.useHVXOps())
345 CCInfo.AnalyzeCallOperands(Outs, CC_Hexagon_HVX);
346 else
347 CCInfo.AnalyzeCallOperands(Outs, CC_Hexagon);
348
349 auto Attr = MF.getFunction().getFnAttribute("disable-tail-calls");
350 if (Attr.getValueAsString() == "true")
351 CLI.IsTailCall = false;
352
353 if (CLI.IsTailCall) {
354 bool StructAttrFlag = MF.getFunction().hasStructRetAttr();
355 CLI.IsTailCall = IsEligibleForTailCallOptimization(Callee, CallConv,
356 IsVarArg, IsStructRet, StructAttrFlag, Outs,
357 OutVals, Ins, DAG);
358 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
359 CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
360 if (VA.isMemLoc()) {
361 CLI.IsTailCall = false;
362 break;
363 }
364 }
365 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << (CLI.IsTailCall ? "Eligible for Tail Call\n"
366 : "Argument must be passed on stack. "
367 "Not eligible for Tail Call\n"));
368 }
369 // Get a count of how many bytes are to be pushed on the stack.
370 unsigned NumBytes = CCInfo.getNextStackOffset();
371 SmallVector<std::pair<unsigned, SDValue>, 16> RegsToPass;
372 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> MemOpChains;
373
374 const HexagonRegisterInfo &HRI = *Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
375 SDValue StackPtr =
376 DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, dl, HRI.getStackRegister(), PtrVT);
377
378 bool NeedsArgAlign = false;
379 unsigned LargestAlignSeen = 0;
380 // Walk the register/memloc assignments, inserting copies/loads.
381 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
382 CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
383 SDValue Arg = OutVals[i];
384 ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Outs[i].Flags;
385 // Record if we need > 8 byte alignment on an argument.
386 bool ArgAlign = Subtarget.isHVXVectorType(VA.getValVT());
387 NeedsArgAlign |= ArgAlign;
388
389 // Promote the value if needed.
390 switch (VA.getLocInfo()) {
391 default:
392 // Loc info must be one of Full, BCvt, SExt, ZExt, or AExt.
393 llvm_unreachable("Unknown loc info!");
394 case CCValAssign::Full:
395 break;
396 case CCValAssign::BCvt:
397 Arg = DAG.getBitcast(VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
398 break;
399 case CCValAssign::SExt:
400 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::SIGN_EXTEND, dl, VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
401 break;
402 case CCValAssign::ZExt:
403 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, dl, VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
404 break;
405 case CCValAssign::AExt:
406 Arg = DAG.getNode(ISD::ANY_EXTEND, dl, VA.getLocVT(), Arg);
407 break;
408 }
409
410 if (VA.isMemLoc()) {
411 unsigned LocMemOffset = VA.getLocMemOffset();
412 SDValue MemAddr = DAG.getConstant(LocMemOffset, dl,
413 StackPtr.getValueType());
414 MemAddr = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, MVT::i32, StackPtr, MemAddr);
415 if (ArgAlign)
416 LargestAlignSeen = std::max(LargestAlignSeen,
417 VA.getLocVT().getStoreSizeInBits() >> 3);
418 if (Flags.isByVal()) {
419 // The argument is a struct passed by value. According to LLVM, "Arg"
420 // is a pointer.
421 MemOpChains.push_back(CreateCopyOfByValArgument(Arg, MemAddr, Chain,
422 Flags, DAG, dl));
423 } else {
424 MachinePointerInfo LocPI = MachinePointerInfo::getStack(
425 DAG.getMachineFunction(), LocMemOffset);
426 SDValue S = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Arg, MemAddr, LocPI);
427 MemOpChains.push_back(S);
428 }
429 continue;
430 }
431
432 // Arguments that can be passed on register must be kept at RegsToPass
433 // vector.
434 if (VA.isRegLoc())
435 RegsToPass.push_back(std::make_pair(VA.getLocReg(), Arg));
436 }
437
438 if (NeedsArgAlign && Subtarget.hasV60Ops()) {
439 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Function needs byte stack align due to call args\n");
440 unsigned VecAlign = HRI.getSpillAlignment(Hexagon::HvxVRRegClass);
441 LargestAlignSeen = std::max(LargestAlignSeen, VecAlign);
442 MFI.ensureMaxAlignment(LargestAlignSeen);
443 }
444 // Transform all store nodes into one single node because all store
445 // nodes are independent of each other.
446 if (!MemOpChains.empty())
447 Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other, MemOpChains);
448
449 SDValue Glue;
450 if (!CLI.IsTailCall) {
451 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_START(Chain, NumBytes, 0, dl);
452 Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
453 }
454
455 // Build a sequence of copy-to-reg nodes chained together with token
456 // chain and flag operands which copy the outgoing args into registers.
457 // The Glue is necessary since all emitted instructions must be
458 // stuck together.
459 if (!CLI.IsTailCall) {
460 for (unsigned i = 0, e = RegsToPass.size(); i != e; ++i) {
461 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, dl, RegsToPass[i].first,
462 RegsToPass[i].second, Glue);
463 Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
464 }
465 } else {
466 // For tail calls lower the arguments to the 'real' stack slot.
467 //
468 // Force all the incoming stack arguments to be loaded from the stack
469 // before any new outgoing arguments are stored to the stack, because the
470 // outgoing stack slots may alias the incoming argument stack slots, and
471 // the alias isn't otherwise explicit. This is slightly more conservative
472 // than necessary, because it means that each store effectively depends
473 // on every argument instead of just those arguments it would clobber.
474 //
475 // Do not flag preceding copytoreg stuff together with the following stuff.
476 Glue = SDValue();
477 for (unsigned i = 0, e = RegsToPass.size(); i != e; ++i) {
478 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, dl, RegsToPass[i].first,
479 RegsToPass[i].second, Glue);
480 Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
481 }
482 Glue = SDValue();
483 }
484
485 bool LongCalls = MF.getSubtarget<HexagonSubtarget>().useLongCalls();
486 unsigned Flags = LongCalls ? HexagonII::HMOTF_ConstExtended : 0;
487
488 // If the callee is a GlobalAddress/ExternalSymbol node (quite common, every
489 // direct call is) turn it into a TargetGlobalAddress/TargetExternalSymbol
490 // node so that legalize doesn't hack it.
491 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *G = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee)) {
492 Callee = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(G->getGlobal(), dl, PtrVT, 0, Flags);
493 } else if (ExternalSymbolSDNode *S =
494 dyn_cast<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Callee)) {
495 Callee = DAG.getTargetExternalFunctionSymbol(S->getSymbol(), Flags);
496 }
497
498 // Returns a chain & a flag for retval copy to use.
499 SDVTList NodeTys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
500 SmallVector<SDValue, 8> Ops;
501 Ops.push_back(Chain);
502 Ops.push_back(Callee);
503
504 // Add argument registers to the end of the list so that they are
505 // known live into the call.
506 for (unsigned i = 0, e = RegsToPass.size(); i != e; ++i) {
507 Ops.push_back(DAG.getRegister(RegsToPass[i].first,
508 RegsToPass[i].second.getValueType()));
509 }
510
511 const uint32_t *Mask = HRI.getCallPreservedMask(MF, CallConv);
512 assert(Mask && "Missing call preserved mask for calling convention");
513 Ops.push_back(DAG.getRegisterMask(Mask));
514
515 if (Glue.getNode())
516 Ops.push_back(Glue);
517
518 if (CLI.IsTailCall) {
519 MFI.setHasTailCall();
520 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::TC_RETURN, dl, NodeTys, Ops);
521 }
522
523 // Set this here because we need to know this for "hasFP" in frame lowering.
524 // The target-independent code calls getFrameRegister before setting it, and
525 // getFrameRegister uses hasFP to determine whether the function has FP.
526 MFI.setHasCalls(true);
527
528 unsigned OpCode = DoesNotReturn ? HexagonISD::CALLnr : HexagonISD::CALL;
529 Chain = DAG.getNode(OpCode, dl, NodeTys, Ops);
530 Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
531
532 // Create the CALLSEQ_END node.
533 Chain = DAG.getCALLSEQ_END(Chain, DAG.getIntPtrConstant(NumBytes, dl, true),
534 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(0, dl, true), Glue, dl);
535 Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
536
537 // Handle result values, copying them out of physregs into vregs that we
538 // return.
539 return LowerCallResult(Chain, Glue, CallConv, IsVarArg, Ins, dl, DAG,
540 InVals, OutVals, Callee);
541}

543/// Returns true by value, base pointer and offset pointer and addressing
544/// mode by reference if this node can be combined with a load / store to
545/// form a post-indexed load / store.
546bool HexagonTargetLowering::getPostIndexedAddressParts(SDNode *N, SDNode *Op,
547 SDValue &Base, SDValue &Offset, ISD::MemIndexedMode &AM,
548 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
549 LSBaseSDNode *LSN = dyn_cast<LSBaseSDNode>(N);
550 if (!LSN)
551 return false;
552 EVT VT = LSN->getMemoryVT();
553 if (!VT.isSimple())
554 return false;
555 bool IsLegalType = VT == MVT::i8 || VT == MVT::i16 || VT == MVT::i32 ||
556 VT == MVT::i64 || VT == MVT::f32 || VT == MVT::f64 ||
557 VT == MVT::v2i16 || VT == MVT::v2i32 || VT == MVT::v4i8 ||
558 VT == MVT::v4i16 || VT == MVT::v8i8 ||
559 Subtarget.isHVXVectorType(VT.getSimpleVT());
560 if (!IsLegalType)
561 return false;
562
563 if (Op->getOpcode() != ISD::ADD)
564 return false;
565 Base = Op->getOperand(0);
566 Offset = Op->getOperand(1);
567 if (!isa<ConstantSDNode>(Offset.getNode()))
568 return false;
569 AM = ISD::POST_INC;
570
571 int32_t V = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Offset.getNode())->getSExtValue();
572 return Subtarget.getInstrInfo()->isValidAutoIncImm(VT, V);
573}

575SDValue
576HexagonTargetLowering::LowerINLINEASM(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
577 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
578 auto &HMFI = *MF.getInfo<HexagonMachineFunctionInfo>();
579 const HexagonRegisterInfo &HRI = *Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
580 unsigned LR = HRI.getRARegister();
581
582 if ((Op.getOpcode() != ISD::INLINEASM &&
583 Op.getOpcode() != ISD::INLINEASM_BR) || HMFI.hasClobberLR())
584 return Op;
585
586 unsigned NumOps = Op.getNumOperands();
587 if (Op.getOperand(NumOps-1).getValueType() == MVT::Glue)
588 --NumOps; // Ignore the flag operand.
589
590 for (unsigned i = InlineAsm::Op_FirstOperand; i != NumOps;) {
591 unsigned Flags = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(i))->getZExtValue();
592 unsigned NumVals = InlineAsm::getNumOperandRegisters(Flags);
593 ++i; // Skip the ID value.
594
595 switch (InlineAsm::getKind(Flags)) {
596 default:
597 llvm_unreachable("Bad flags!");
598 case InlineAsm::Kind_RegUse:
599 case InlineAsm::Kind_Imm:
600 case InlineAsm::Kind_Mem:
601 i += NumVals;
602 break;
603 case InlineAsm::Kind_Clobber:
604 case InlineAsm::Kind_RegDef:
605 case InlineAsm::Kind_RegDefEarlyClobber: {
606 for (; NumVals; --NumVals, ++i) {
607 unsigned Reg = cast<RegisterSDNode>(Op.getOperand(i))->getReg();
608 if (Reg != LR)
609 continue;
610 HMFI.setHasClobberLR(true);
611 return Op;
612 }
613 break;
614 }
615 }
616 }
617
618 return Op;
619}

621// Need to transform ISD::PREFETCH into something that doesn't inherit
622// all of the properties of ISD::PREFETCH, specifically SDNPMayLoad and
623// SDNPMayStore.
624SDValue HexagonTargetLowering::LowerPREFETCH(SDValue Op,
625 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
626 SDValue Chain = Op.getOperand(0);
627 SDValue Addr = Op.getOperand(1);
628 // Lower it to DCFETCH($reg, #0). A "pat" will try to merge the offset in,
629 // if the "reg" is fed by an "add".
630 SDLoc DL(Op);
631 SDValue Zero = DAG.getConstant(0, DL, MVT::i32);
632 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::DCFETCH, DL, MVT::Other, Chain, Addr, Zero);
633}

635// Custom-handle ISD::READCYCLECOUNTER because the target-independent SDNode
636// is marked as having side-effects, while the register read on Hexagon does
637// not have any. TableGen refuses to accept the direct pattern from that node
638// to the A4_tfrcpp.
639SDValue HexagonTargetLowering::LowerREADCYCLECOUNTER(SDValue Op,
640 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
641 SDValue Chain = Op.getOperand(0);
642 SDLoc dl(Op);
643 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::Other);
644 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::READCYCLE, dl, VTs, Chain);

661SDValue
662HexagonTargetLowering::LowerDYNAMIC_STACKALLOC(SDValue Op,
663 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
664 SDValue Chain = Op.getOperand(0);
665 SDValue Size = Op.getOperand(1);
666 SDValue Align = Op.getOperand(2);
667 SDLoc dl(Op);
668
669 ConstantSDNode *AlignConst = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Align);
670 assert(AlignConst && "Non-constant Align in LowerDYNAMIC_STACKALLOC");
671
672 unsigned A = AlignConst->getSExtValue();
673 auto &HFI = *Subtarget.getFrameLowering();
674 // "Zero" means natural stack alignment.
675 if (A == 0)
676 A = HFI.getStackAlignment();
677
678 LLVM_DEBUG({
679 dbgs () << __func__ << " Align: " << A << " Size: ";
680 Size.getNode()->dump(&DAG);
681 dbgs() << "\n";
682 });
683
684 SDValue AC = DAG.getConstant(A, dl, MVT::i32);
685 SDVTList VTs = DAG.getVTList(MVT::i32, MVT::Other);
686 SDValue AA = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::ALLOCA, dl, VTs, Chain, Size, AC);
687
688 DAG.ReplaceAllUsesOfValueWith(Op, AA);
689 return AA;
690}
691
692SDValue HexagonTargetLowering::LowerFormalArguments(
693 SDValue Chain, CallingConv::ID CallConv, bool IsVarArg,
694 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins, const SDLoc &dl,
695 SelectionDAG &DAG, SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &InVals) const {
696 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
697 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
698 MachineRegisterInfo &MRI = MF.getRegInfo();
699
700 // Assign locations to all of the incoming arguments.
701 SmallVector<CCValAssign, 16> ArgLocs;
702 HexagonCCState CCInfo(CallConv, IsVarArg, MF, ArgLocs, *DAG.getContext(),
703 MF.getFunction().getFunctionType()->getNumParams());
704
705 if (Subtarget.useHVXOps())
706 CCInfo.AnalyzeFormalArguments(Ins, CC_Hexagon_HVX);
707 else
708 CCInfo.AnalyzeFormalArguments(Ins, CC_Hexagon);
709
710 // For LLVM, in the case when returning a struct by value (>8byte),
711 // the first argument is a pointer that points to the location on caller's
712 // stack where the return value will be stored. For Hexagon, the location on
713 // caller's stack is passed only when the struct size is smaller than (and
714 // equal to) 8 bytes. If not, no address will be passed into callee and
715 // callee return the result direclty through R0/R1.
716
717 auto &HMFI = *MF.getInfo<HexagonMachineFunctionInfo>();
718
719 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ArgLocs.size(); i != e; ++i) {
720 CCValAssign &VA = ArgLocs[i];
721 ISD::ArgFlagsTy Flags = Ins[i].Flags;
722 bool ByVal = Flags.isByVal();
723
724 // Arguments passed in registers:
725 // 1. 32- and 64-bit values and HVX vectors are passed directly,
726 // 2. Large structs are passed via an address, and the address is
727 // passed in a register.
728 if (VA.isRegLoc() && ByVal && Flags.getByValSize() <= 8)
729 llvm_unreachable("ByValSize must be bigger than 8 bytes");
730
731 bool InReg = VA.isRegLoc() &&
732 (!ByVal || (ByVal && Flags.getByValSize() > 8));
733
734 if (InReg) {
735 MVT RegVT = VA.getLocVT();
736 if (VA.getLocInfo() == CCValAssign::BCvt)
737 RegVT = VA.getValVT();
738
739 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = getRegClassFor(RegVT);
740 unsigned VReg = MRI.createVirtualRegister(RC);
741 SDValue Copy = DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, dl, VReg, RegVT);
742
743 // Treat values of type MVT::i1 specially: they are passed in
744 // registers of type i32, but they need to remain as values of
745 // type i1 for consistency of the argument lowering.
746 if (VA.getValVT() == MVT::i1) {
747 assert(RegVT.getSizeInBits() <= 32);
748 SDValue T = DAG.getNode(ISD::AND, dl, RegVT,
749 Copy, DAG.getConstant(1, dl, RegVT));
750 Copy = DAG.getSetCC(dl, MVT::i1, T, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, RegVT),
751 ISD::SETNE);
752 } else {
753#ifndef NDEBUG
754 unsigned RegSize = RegVT.getSizeInBits();
755 assert(RegSize == 32 || RegSize == 64 ||
756 Subtarget.isHVXVectorType(RegVT));
757#endif
758 }
759 InVals.push_back(Copy);
760 MRI.addLiveIn(VA.getLocReg(), VReg);
761 } else {
762 assert(VA.isMemLoc() && "Argument should be passed in memory");
763
764 // If it's a byval parameter, then we need to compute the
765 // "real" size, not the size of the pointer.
766 unsigned ObjSize = Flags.isByVal()
767 ? Flags.getByValSize()
768 : VA.getLocVT().getStoreSizeInBits() / 8;
769
770 // Create the frame index object for this incoming parameter.
771 int Offset = HEXAGON_LRFP_SIZE + VA.getLocMemOffset();
772 int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(ObjSize, Offset, true);
773 SDValue FIN = DAG.getFrameIndex(FI, MVT::i32);
774
775 if (Flags.isByVal()) {
776 // If it's a pass-by-value aggregate, then do not dereference the stack
777 // location. Instead, we should generate a reference to the stack
778 // location.
779 InVals.push_back(FIN);
780 } else {
781 SDValue L = DAG.getLoad(VA.getValVT(), dl, Chain, FIN,
782 MachinePointerInfo::getFixedStack(MF, FI, 0));
783 InVals.push_back(L);
784 }
785 }
786 }
787
788
789 if (IsVarArg) {
790 // This will point to the next argument passed via stack.
791 int Offset = HEXAGON_LRFP_SIZE + CCInfo.getNextStackOffset();
792 int FI = MFI.CreateFixedObject(Hexagon_PointerSize, Offset, true);
793 HMFI.setVarArgsFrameIndex(FI);
794 }
795
796 return Chain;
797}

800HexagonTargetLowering::LowerVASTART(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
801 // VASTART stores the address of the VarArgsFrameIndex slot into the
802 // memory location argument.
803 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
804 HexagonMachineFunctionInfo *QFI = MF.getInfo<HexagonMachineFunctionInfo>();
805 SDValue Addr = DAG.getFrameIndex(QFI->getVarArgsFrameIndex(), MVT::i32);
806 const Value *SV = cast<SrcValueSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->getValue();

810
811SDValue HexagonTargetLowering::LowerSETCC(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
812 const SDLoc &dl(Op);
813 SDValue LHS = Op.getOperand(0);
814 SDValue RHS = Op.getOperand(1);
815 ISD::CondCode CC = cast<CondCodeSDNode>(Op.getOperand(2))->get();
816 MVT ResTy = ty(Op);
817 MVT OpTy = ty(LHS);
818
819 if (OpTy == MVT::v2i16 || OpTy == MVT::v4i8) {
820 MVT ElemTy = OpTy.getVectorElementType();
821 assert(ElemTy.isScalarInteger());
822 MVT WideTy = MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::getIntegerVT(2*ElemTy.getSizeInBits()),
823 OpTy.getVectorNumElements());
824 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, ResTy,
825 DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(LHS, SDLoc(LHS), WideTy),
826 DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(RHS, SDLoc(RHS), WideTy), CC);
827 }
828
829 // Treat all other vector types as legal.
830 if (ResTy.isVector())
831 return Op;
832
833 // Comparisons of short integers should use sign-extend, not zero-extend,
834 // since we can represent small negative values in the compare instructions.
835 // The LLVM default is to use zero-extend arbitrarily in these cases.
836 auto isSExtFree = [this](SDValue N) {
837 switch (N.getOpcode()) {
838 case ISD::TRUNCATE: {
839 // A sign-extend of a truncate of a sign-extend is free.
840 SDValue Op = N.getOperand(0);
841 if (Op.getOpcode() != ISD::AssertSext)
842 return false;
843 EVT OrigTy = cast<VTSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1))->getVT();
844 unsigned ThisBW = ty(N).getSizeInBits();
845 unsigned OrigBW = OrigTy.getSizeInBits();
846 // The type that was sign-extended to get the AssertSext must be
847 // narrower than the type of N (so that N has still the same value
848 // as the original).
849 return ThisBW >= OrigBW;
850 }
851 case ISD::LOAD:
852 // We have sign-extended loads.
853 return true;
854 }
855 return false;
856 };
857
858 if (OpTy == MVT::i8 || OpTy == MVT::i16) {
859 ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(RHS);
860 bool IsNegative = C && C->getAPIntValue().isNegative();
861 if (IsNegative || isSExtFree(LHS) || isSExtFree(RHS))
862 return DAG.getSetCC(dl, ResTy,
863 DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(LHS, SDLoc(LHS), MVT::i32),
864 DAG.getSExtOrTrunc(RHS, SDLoc(RHS), MVT::i32), CC);
865 }
866
867 return SDValue();
868}

870SDValue
871HexagonTargetLowering::LowerVSELECT(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
872 SDValue PredOp = Op.getOperand(0);
873 SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1), Op2 = Op.getOperand(2);
874 EVT OpVT = Op1.getValueType();
875 SDLoc DL(Op);
876
877 if (OpVT == MVT::v2i16) {
878 SDValue X1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MVT::v2i32, Op1);
879 SDValue X2 = DAG.getNode(ISD::ZERO_EXTEND, DL, MVT::v2i32, Op2);
880 SDValue SL = DAG.getNode(ISD::VSELECT, DL, MVT::v2i32, PredOp, X1, X2);
881 SDValue TR = DAG.getNode(ISD::TRUNCATE, DL, MVT::v2i16, SL);
882 return TR;
883 }
884
885 return SDValue();
886}

888static Constant *convert_i1_to_i8(const Constant *ConstVal) {
889 SmallVector<Constant *, 128> NewConst;
890 const ConstantVector *CV = dyn_cast<ConstantVector>(ConstVal);
891 if (!CV)
892 return nullptr;
893
894 LLVMContext &Ctx = ConstVal->getContext();
895 IRBuilder<> IRB(Ctx);
896 unsigned NumVectorElements = CV->getNumOperands();
897 assert(isPowerOf2_32(NumVectorElements) &&
898 "conversion only supported for pow2 VectorSize!");
899
900 for (unsigned i = 0; i < NumVectorElements / 8; ++i) {
901 uint8_t x = 0;
902 for (unsigned j = 0; j < 8; ++j) {
903 uint8_t y = CV->getOperand(i * 8 + j)->getUniqueInteger().getZExtValue();
904 x |= y << (7 - j);
905 }
906 assert((x == 0 || x == 255) && "Either all 0's or all 1's expected!");
907 NewConst.push_back(IRB.getInt8(x));
908 }
909 return ConstantVector::get(NewConst);
910}

912SDValue
913HexagonTargetLowering::LowerConstantPool(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
914 EVT ValTy = Op.getValueType();
915 ConstantPoolSDNode *CPN = cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(Op);
916 Constant *CVal = nullptr;
917 bool isVTi1Type = false;
918 if (const Constant *ConstVal = dyn_cast<Constant>(CPN->getConstVal())) {
919 Type *CValTy = ConstVal->getType();
920 if (CValTy->isVectorTy() &&
921 CValTy->getVectorElementType()->isIntegerTy(1)) {
922 CVal = convert_i1_to_i8(ConstVal);
923 isVTi1Type = (CVal != nullptr);
924 }
925 }
926 unsigned Align = CPN->getAlignment();
927 bool IsPositionIndependent = isPositionIndependent();
928 unsigned char TF = IsPositionIndependent ? HexagonII::MO_PCREL : 0;
929
930 unsigned Offset = 0;
931 SDValue T;
932 if (CPN->isMachineConstantPoolEntry())
933 T = DAG.getTargetConstantPool(CPN->getMachineCPVal(), ValTy, Align, Offset,
934 TF);
935 else if (isVTi1Type)
936 T = DAG.getTargetConstantPool(CVal, ValTy, Align, Offset, TF);
937 else
938 T = DAG.getTargetConstantPool(CPN->getConstVal(), ValTy, Align, Offset, TF);
939
940 assert(cast<ConstantPoolSDNode>(T)->getTargetFlags() == TF &&
941 "Inconsistent target flag encountered");
942
943 if (IsPositionIndependent)
944 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::AT_PCREL, SDLoc(Op), ValTy, T);
945 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::CP, SDLoc(Op), ValTy, T);
946}

961SDValue
962HexagonTargetLowering::LowerRETURNADDR(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
963 const HexagonRegisterInfo &HRI = *Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
964 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
965 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
966 MFI.setReturnAddressIsTaken(true);
967
968 if (verifyReturnAddressArgumentIsConstant(Op, DAG))
969 return SDValue();
970
971 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
972 SDLoc dl(Op);
973 unsigned Depth = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
974 if (Depth) {
975 SDValue FrameAddr = LowerFRAMEADDR(Op, DAG);
976 SDValue Offset = DAG.getConstant(4, dl, MVT::i32);
977 return DAG.getLoad(VT, dl, DAG.getEntryNode(),
978 DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, VT, FrameAddr, Offset),
979 MachinePointerInfo());
980 }
981
982 // Return LR, which contains the return address. Mark it an implicit live-in.
983 unsigned Reg = MF.addLiveIn(HRI.getRARegister(), getRegClassFor(MVT::i32));
984 return DAG.getCopyFromReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Reg, VT);
985}

987SDValue
988HexagonTargetLowering::LowerFRAMEADDR(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
989 const HexagonRegisterInfo &HRI = *Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
990 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFrameInfo();
991 MFI.setFrameAddressIsTaken(true);
992
993 EVT VT = Op.getValueType();
994 SDLoc dl(Op);
995 unsigned Depth = cast<ConstantSDNode>(Op.getOperand(0))->getZExtValue();
996 SDValue FrameAddr = DAG.getCopyFromReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl,
997 HRI.getFrameRegister(), VT);
998 while (Depth--)
999 FrameAddr = DAG.getLoad(VT, dl, DAG.getEntryNode(), FrameAddr,
1000 MachinePointerInfo());
1001 return FrameAddr;
1002}

1010SDValue
1011HexagonTargetLowering::LowerGLOBALADDRESS(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1012 SDLoc dl(Op);
1013 auto *GAN = cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Op);
1014 auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
1015 auto *GV = GAN->getGlobal();
1016 int64_t Offset = GAN->getOffset();
1017
1018 auto &HLOF = *HTM.getObjFileLowering();
1019 Reloc::Model RM = HTM.getRelocationModel();
1020
1021 if (RM == Reloc::Static) {
1022 SDValue GA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, dl, PtrVT, Offset);
1023 const GlobalObject *GO = GV->getBaseObject();
1024 if (GO && Subtarget.useSmallData() && HLOF.isGlobalInSmallSection(GO, HTM))
1025 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::CONST32_GP, dl, PtrVT, GA);
1026 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::CONST32, dl, PtrVT, GA);
1027 }
1028
1029 bool UsePCRel = getTargetMachine().shouldAssumeDSOLocal(*GV->getParent(), GV);
1030 if (UsePCRel) {
1031 SDValue GA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, dl, PtrVT, Offset,
1032 HexagonII::MO_PCREL);
1033 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::AT_PCREL, dl, PtrVT, GA);
1034 }
1035
1036 // Use GOT index.
1037 SDValue GOT = DAG.getGLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE(PtrVT);
1038 SDValue GA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GV, dl, PtrVT, 0, HexagonII::MO_GOT);
1039 SDValue Off = DAG.getConstant(Offset, dl, MVT::i32);
1040 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::AT_GOT, dl, PtrVT, GOT, GA, Off);
1041}

1069SDValue
1070HexagonTargetLowering::GetDynamicTLSAddr(SelectionDAG &DAG, SDValue Chain,
1071 GlobalAddressSDNode *GA, SDValue Glue, EVT PtrVT, unsigned ReturnReg,
1072 unsigned char OperandFlags) const {
1073 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
1074 MachineFrameInfo &MFI = MF.getFrameInfo();
1075 SDVTList NodeTys = DAG.getVTList(MVT::Other, MVT::Glue);
1076 SDLoc dl(GA);
1077 SDValue TGA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GA->getGlobal(), dl,
1078 GA->getValueType(0),
1079 GA->getOffset(),
1080 OperandFlags);
1081 // Create Operands for the call.The Operands should have the following:
1082 // 1. Chain SDValue
1083 // 2. Callee which in this case is the Global address value.
1084 // 3. Registers live into the call.In this case its R0, as we
1085 // have just one argument to be passed.
1086 // 4. Glue.
1087 // Note: The order is important.
1088
1089 const auto &HRI = *Subtarget.getRegisterInfo();
1090 const uint32_t *Mask = HRI.getCallPreservedMask(MF, CallingConv::C);
1091 assert(Mask && "Missing call preserved mask for calling convention");
1092 SDValue Ops[] = { Chain, TGA, DAG.getRegister(Hexagon::R0, PtrVT),
1093 DAG.getRegisterMask(Mask), Glue };
1094 Chain = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::CALL, dl, NodeTys, Ops);
1095
1096 // Inform MFI that function has calls.
1097 MFI.setAdjustsStack(true);
1098
1099 Glue = Chain.getValue(1);
1100 return DAG.getCopyFromReg(Chain, dl, ReturnReg, PtrVT, Glue);
1101}
1102
1103//
1104// Lower using the intial executable model for TLS addresses
1105//
1106SDValue
1107HexagonTargetLowering::LowerToTLSInitialExecModel(GlobalAddressSDNode *GA,
1108 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1109 SDLoc dl(GA);
1110 int64_t Offset = GA->getOffset();
1111 auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
1112
1113 // Get the thread pointer.
1114 SDValue TP = DAG.getCopyFromReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Hexagon::UGP, PtrVT);
1115
1116 bool IsPositionIndependent = isPositionIndependent();
1117 unsigned char TF =
1118 IsPositionIndependent ? HexagonII::MO_IEGOT : HexagonII::MO_IE;
1119
1120 // First generate the TLS symbol address
1121 SDValue TGA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GA->getGlobal(), dl, PtrVT,
1122 Offset, TF);
1123
1124 SDValue Sym = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::CONST32, dl, PtrVT, TGA);
1125
1126 if (IsPositionIndependent) {
1127 // Generate the GOT pointer in case of position independent code
1128 SDValue GOT = LowerGLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE(Sym, DAG);
1129
1130 // Add the TLS Symbol address to GOT pointer.This gives
1131 // GOT relative relocation for the symbol.
1132 Sym = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, PtrVT, GOT, Sym);
1133 }
1134
1135 // Load the offset value for TLS symbol.This offset is relative to
1136 // thread pointer.
1137 SDValue LoadOffset =
1138 DAG.getLoad(PtrVT, dl, DAG.getEntryNode(), Sym, MachinePointerInfo());
1139
1140 // Address of the thread local variable is the add of thread
1141 // pointer and the offset of the variable.
1142 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, PtrVT, TP, LoadOffset);
1143}
1144
1145//
1146// Lower using the local executable model for TLS addresses
1147//
1148SDValue
1149HexagonTargetLowering::LowerToTLSLocalExecModel(GlobalAddressSDNode *GA,
1150 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1151 SDLoc dl(GA);
1152 int64_t Offset = GA->getOffset();
1153 auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
1154
1155 // Get the thread pointer.
1156 SDValue TP = DAG.getCopyFromReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Hexagon::UGP, PtrVT);
1157 // Generate the TLS symbol address
1158 SDValue TGA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GA->getGlobal(), dl, PtrVT, Offset,
1159 HexagonII::MO_TPREL);
1160 SDValue Sym = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::CONST32, dl, PtrVT, TGA);
1161
1162 // Address of the thread local variable is the add of thread
1163 // pointer and the offset of the variable.
1164 return DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, PtrVT, TP, Sym);
1165}
1166
1167//
1168// Lower using the general dynamic model for TLS addresses
1169//
1170SDValue
1171HexagonTargetLowering::LowerToTLSGeneralDynamicModel(GlobalAddressSDNode *GA,
1172 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1173 SDLoc dl(GA);
1174 int64_t Offset = GA->getOffset();
1175 auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
1176
1177 // First generate the TLS symbol address
1178 SDValue TGA = DAG.getTargetGlobalAddress(GA->getGlobal(), dl, PtrVT, Offset,
1179 HexagonII::MO_GDGOT);
1180
1181 // Then, generate the GOT pointer
1182 SDValue GOT = LowerGLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE(TGA, DAG);
1183
1184 // Add the TLS symbol and the GOT pointer
1185 SDValue Sym = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::CONST32, dl, PtrVT, TGA);
1186 SDValue Chain = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, PtrVT, GOT, Sym);
1187
1188 // Copy over the argument to R0
1189 SDValue InFlag;
1190 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(DAG.getEntryNode(), dl, Hexagon::R0, Chain, InFlag);
1191 InFlag = Chain.getValue(1);
1192
1193 unsigned Flags =
1194 static_cast<const HexagonSubtarget &>(DAG.getSubtarget()).useLongCalls()
1195 ? HexagonII::MO_GDPLT | HexagonII::HMOTF_ConstExtended
1196 : HexagonII::MO_GDPLT;
1197
1198 return GetDynamicTLSAddr(DAG, Chain, GA, InFlag, PtrVT,
1199 Hexagon::R0, Flags);
1200}
1201
1202//
1203// Lower TLS addresses.
1204//
1205// For now for dynamic models, we only support the general dynamic model.
1206//
1207SDValue
1208HexagonTargetLowering::LowerGlobalTLSAddress(SDValue Op,
1209 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
1210 GlobalAddressSDNode *GA = cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Op);
1211
1212 switch (HTM.getTLSModel(GA->getGlobal())) {
1213 case TLSModel::GeneralDynamic:
1214 case TLSModel::LocalDynamic:
1215 return LowerToTLSGeneralDynamicModel(GA, DAG);
1216 case TLSModel::InitialExec:
1217 return LowerToTLSInitialExecModel(GA, DAG);
1218 case TLSModel::LocalExec:
1219 return LowerToTLSLocalExecModel(GA, DAG);
1220 }
1221 llvm_unreachable("Bogus TLS model");
1222}

1603 }
1604
1605 if (FastMath)
1606 setLibcallName(RTLIB::SQRT_F32, "__hexagon_fast2_sqrtf");
1607 else
1608 setLibcallName(RTLIB::SQRT_F32, "__hexagon_sqrtf");
1609
1610 // These cause problems when the shift amount is non-constant.
1611 setLibcallName(RTLIB::SHL_I128, nullptr);
1612 setLibcallName(RTLIB::SRL_I128, nullptr);
1613 setLibcallName(RTLIB::SRA_I128, nullptr);

1663
1664void
1665HexagonTargetLowering::validateConstPtrAlignment(SDValue Ptr, const SDLoc &dl,
1666 unsigned NeedAlign) const {
1667 auto *CA = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(Ptr);
1668 if (!CA)
1669 return;
1670 unsigned Addr = CA->getZExtValue();
1671 unsigned HaveAlign = Addr != 0 ? 1u << countTrailingZeros(Addr) : NeedAlign;
1672 if (HaveAlign < NeedAlign) {
1673 std::string ErrMsg;
1674 raw_string_ostream O(ErrMsg);
1675 O << "Misaligned constant address: " << format_hex(Addr, 10)
1676 << " has alignment " << HaveAlign
1677 << ", but the memory access requires " << NeedAlign;
1678 if (DebugLoc DL = dl.getDebugLoc())
1679 DL.print(O << ", at ");
1680 report_fatal_error(O.str());
1681 }
1682}
1683
1684// Bit-reverse Load Intrinsic: Check if the instruction is a bit reverse load
1685// intrinsic.
1686static bool isBrevLdIntrinsic(const Value *Inst) {
1687 unsigned ID = cast<IntrinsicInst>(Inst)->getIntrinsicID();
1688 return (ID == Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrd_pbr ||
1689 ID == Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadri_pbr ||
1690 ID == Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrh_pbr ||
1691 ID == Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadruh_pbr ||
1692 ID == Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrb_pbr ||
1693 ID == Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrub_pbr);
1694}
1695
1696// Bit-reverse Load Intrinsic :Crawl up and figure out the object from previous
1697// instruction. So far we only handle bitcast, extract value and bit reverse
1698// load intrinsic instructions. Should we handle CGEP ?
1699static Value *getBrevLdObject(Value *V) {
1700 if (Operator::getOpcode(V) == Instruction::ExtractValue ||
1701 Operator::getOpcode(V) == Instruction::BitCast)
1702 V = cast<Operator>(V)->getOperand(0);
1703 else if (isa<IntrinsicInst>(V) && isBrevLdIntrinsic(V))
1704 V = cast<Instruction>(V)->getOperand(0);
1705 return V;
1706}
1707
1708// Bit-reverse Load Intrinsic: For a PHI Node return either an incoming edge or
1709// a back edge. If the back edge comes from the intrinsic itself, the incoming
1710// edge is returned.
1711static Value *returnEdge(const PHINode *PN, Value *IntrBaseVal) {
1712 const BasicBlock *Parent = PN->getParent();
1713 int Idx = -1;
1714 for (unsigned i = 0, e = PN->getNumIncomingValues(); i < e; ++i) {
1715 BasicBlock *Blk = PN->getIncomingBlock(i);
1716 // Determine if the back edge is originated from intrinsic.
1717 if (Blk == Parent) {
1718 Value *BackEdgeVal = PN->getIncomingValue(i);
1719 Value *BaseVal;
1720 // Loop over till we return the same Value or we hit the IntrBaseVal.
1721 do {
1722 BaseVal = BackEdgeVal;
1723 BackEdgeVal = getBrevLdObject(BackEdgeVal);
1724 } while ((BaseVal != BackEdgeVal) && (IntrBaseVal != BackEdgeVal));
1725 // If the getBrevLdObject returns IntrBaseVal, we should return the
1726 // incoming edge.
1727 if (IntrBaseVal == BackEdgeVal)
1728 continue;
1729 Idx = i;
1730 break;
1731 } else // Set the node to incoming edge.
1732 Idx = i;
1733 }
1734 assert(Idx >= 0 && "Unexpected index to incoming argument in PHI");
1735 return PN->getIncomingValue(Idx);
1736}
1737
1738// Bit-reverse Load Intrinsic: Figure out the underlying object the base
1739// pointer points to, for the bit-reverse load intrinsic. Setting this to
1740// memoperand might help alias analysis to figure out the dependencies.
1741static Value *getUnderLyingObjectForBrevLdIntr(Value *V) {
1742 Value *IntrBaseVal = V;
1743 Value *BaseVal;
1744 // Loop over till we return the same Value, implies we either figure out
1745 // the object or we hit a PHI
1746 do {
1747 BaseVal = V;
1748 V = getBrevLdObject(V);
1749 } while (BaseVal != V);
1750
1751 // Identify the object from PHINode.
1752 if (const PHINode *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(V))
1753 return returnEdge(PN, IntrBaseVal);
1754 // For non PHI nodes, the object is the last value returned by getBrevLdObject
1755 else
1756 return V;
1757}
1758
1759/// Given an intrinsic, checks if on the target the intrinsic will need to map
1760/// to a MemIntrinsicNode (touches memory). If this is the case, it returns
1761/// true and store the intrinsic information into the IntrinsicInfo that was
1762/// passed to the function.
1763bool HexagonTargetLowering::getTgtMemIntrinsic(IntrinsicInfo &Info,
1764 const CallInst &I,
1765 MachineFunction &MF,
1766 unsigned Intrinsic) const {
1767 switch (Intrinsic) {
1768 case Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrd_pbr:
1769 case Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadri_pbr:
1770 case Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrh_pbr:
1771 case Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadruh_pbr:
1772 case Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrb_pbr:
1773 case Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadrub_pbr: {
1774 Info.opc = ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN;
1775 auto &DL = I.getCalledFunction()->getParent()->getDataLayout();
1776 auto &Cont = I.getCalledFunction()->getParent()->getContext();
1777 // The intrinsic function call is of the form { ElTy, i8* }
1778 // @llvm.hexagon.L2.loadXX.pbr(i8*, i32). The pointer and memory access type
1779 // should be derived from ElTy.
1780 Type *ElTy = I.getCalledFunction()->getReturnType()->getStructElementType(0);
1781 Info.memVT = MVT::getVT(ElTy);
1782 llvm::Value *BasePtrVal = I.getOperand(0);
1783 Info.ptrVal = getUnderLyingObjectForBrevLdIntr(BasePtrVal);
1784 // The offset value comes through Modifier register. For now, assume the
1785 // offset is 0.
1786 Info.offset = 0;
1787 Info.align = DL.getABITypeAlignment(Info.memVT.getTypeForEVT(Cont));
1788 Info.flags = MachineMemOperand::MOLoad;
1789 return true;
1790 }
1791 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermw:
1792 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermw_128B:
1793 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermh:
1794 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermh_128B:
1795 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermhw:
1796 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermhw_128B:
1797 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermwq:
1798 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermwq_128B:
1799 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermhq:
1800 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermhq_128B:
1801 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermhwq:
1802 case Intrinsic::hexagon_V6_vgathermhwq_128B: {
1803 const Module &M = *I.getParent()->getParent()->getParent();
1804 Info.opc = ISD::INTRINSIC_W_CHAIN;
1805 Type *VecTy = I.getArgOperand(1)->getType();
1806 Info.memVT = MVT::getVT(VecTy);
1807 Info.ptrVal = I.getArgOperand(0);
1808 Info.offset = 0;
1809 Info.align = M.getDataLayout().getTypeAllocSizeInBits(VecTy) / 8;
1810 Info.flags = MachineMemOperand::MOLoad |
1811 MachineMemOperand::MOStore |
1812 MachineMemOperand::MOVolatile;
1813 return true;
1814 }
1815 default:
1816 break;
1817 }
1818 return false;
1819}

1845
1846TargetLoweringBase::LegalizeTypeAction
1847HexagonTargetLowering::getPreferredVectorAction(MVT VT) const {
1848 if (VT.getVectorNumElements() == 1)
1849 return TargetLoweringBase::TypeScalarizeVector;
1850
1851 // Always widen vectors of i1.
1852 MVT ElemTy = VT.getVectorElementType();
1853 if (ElemTy == MVT::i1)
1854 return TargetLoweringBase::TypeWidenVector;
1855
1856 if (Subtarget.useHVXOps()) {
1857 // If the size of VT is at least half of the vector length,
1858 // widen the vector. Note: the threshold was not selected in
1859 // any scientific way.
1860 ArrayRef<MVT> Tys = Subtarget.getHVXElementTypes();
1861 if (llvm::find(Tys, ElemTy) != Tys.end()) {
1862 unsigned HwWidth = 8*Subtarget.getVectorLength();
1863 unsigned VecWidth = VT.getSizeInBits();
1864 if (VecWidth >= HwWidth/2 && VecWidth < HwWidth)
1865 return TargetLoweringBase::TypeWidenVector;
1866 }
1867 }
1868 return TargetLoweringBase::TypeSplitVector;
1869}

1871std::pair<SDValue, int>
1872HexagonTargetLowering::getBaseAndOffset(SDValue Addr) const {
1873 if (Addr.getOpcode() == ISD::ADD) {
1874 SDValue Op1 = Addr.getOperand(1);
1875 if (auto *CN = dyn_cast<const ConstantSDNode>(Op1.getNode()))
1876 return { Addr.getOperand(0), CN->getSExtValue() };
1877 }
1878 return { Addr, 0 };
1879}

1881// Lower a vector shuffle (V1, V2, V3). V1 and V2 are the two vectors
1882// to select data from, V3 is the permutation.
1883SDValue
1884HexagonTargetLowering::LowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG)
1885 const {
1886 const auto *SVN = cast<ShuffleVectorSDNode>(Op);
1887 ArrayRef<int> AM = SVN->getMask();
1888 assert(AM.size() <= 8 && "Unexpected shuffle mask");
1889 unsigned VecLen = AM.size();
1890
1891 MVT VecTy = ty(Op);
1892 assert(!Subtarget.isHVXVectorType(VecTy, true) &&
1893 "HVX shuffles should be legal");
1894 assert(VecTy.getSizeInBits() <= 64 && "Unexpected vector length");
1895
1896 SDValue Op0 = Op.getOperand(0);
1897 SDValue Op1 = Op.getOperand(1);
1898 const SDLoc &dl(Op);
1899
1900 // If the inputs are not the same as the output, bail. This is not an
1901 // error situation, but complicates the handling and the default expansion
1902 // (into BUILD_VECTOR) should be adequate.
1903 if (ty(Op0) != VecTy || ty(Op1) != VecTy)
1904 return SDValue();
1905
1906 // Normalize the mask so that the first non-negative index comes from
1907 // the first operand.
1908 SmallVector<int,8> Mask(AM.begin(), AM.end());
1909 unsigned F = llvm::find_if(AM, [](int M) { return M >= 0; }) - AM.data();
1910 if (F == AM.size())
1911 return DAG.getUNDEF(VecTy);
1912 if (AM[F] >= int(VecLen)) {
1913 ShuffleVectorSDNode::commuteMask(Mask);
1914 std::swap(Op0, Op1);
1915 }
1916
1917 // Express the shuffle mask in terms of bytes.
1918 SmallVector<int,8> ByteMask;
1919 unsigned ElemBytes = VecTy.getVectorElementType().getSizeInBits() / 8;
1920 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Mask.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1921 int M = Mask[i];
1922 if (M < 0) {
1923 for (unsigned j = 0; j != ElemBytes; ++j)
1924 ByteMask.push_back(-1);
1925 } else {
1926 for (unsigned j = 0; j != ElemBytes; ++j)
1927 ByteMask.push_back(M*ElemBytes + j);
1928 }
1929 }
1930 assert(ByteMask.size() <= 8);
1931
1932 // All non-undef (non-negative) indexes are well within [0..127], so they
1933 // fit in a single byte. Build two 64-bit words:
1934 // - MaskIdx where each byte is the corresponding index (for non-negative
1935 // indexes), and 0xFF for negative indexes, and
1936 // - MaskUnd that has 0xFF for each negative index.
1937 uint64_t MaskIdx = 0;
1938 uint64_t MaskUnd = 0;
1939 for (unsigned i = 0, e = ByteMask.size(); i != e; ++i) {
1940 unsigned S = 8*i;
1941 uint64_t M = ByteMask[i] & 0xFF;
1942 if (M == 0xFF)
1943 MaskUnd |= M << S;
1944 MaskIdx |= M << S;
1945 }
1946
1947 if (ByteMask.size() == 4) {
1948 // Identity.
1949 if (MaskIdx == (0x03020100 | MaskUnd))
1950 return Op0;
1951 // Byte swap.
1952 if (MaskIdx == (0x00010203 | MaskUnd)) {
1953 SDValue T0 = DAG.getBitcast(MVT::i32, Op0);
1954 SDValue T1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BSWAP, dl, MVT::i32, T0);
1955 return DAG.getBitcast(VecTy, T1);
1956 }
1957
1958 // Byte packs.
1959 SDValue Concat10 = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::COMBINE, dl,
1960 typeJoin({ty(Op1), ty(Op0)}), {Op1, Op0});
1961 if (MaskIdx == (0x06040200 | MaskUnd))
1962 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_vtrunehb, dl, VecTy, {Concat10}, DAG);
1963 if (MaskIdx == (0x07050301 | MaskUnd))
1964 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_vtrunohb, dl, VecTy, {Concat10}, DAG);
1965
1966 SDValue Concat01 = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::COMBINE, dl,
1967 typeJoin({ty(Op0), ty(Op1)}), {Op0, Op1});
1968 if (MaskIdx == (0x02000604 | MaskUnd))
1969 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_vtrunehb, dl, VecTy, {Concat01}, DAG);
1970 if (MaskIdx == (0x03010705 | MaskUnd))
1971 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_vtrunohb, dl, VecTy, {Concat01}, DAG);
1972 }
1973
1974 if (ByteMask.size() == 8) {
1975 // Identity.
1976 if (MaskIdx == (0x0706050403020100ull | MaskUnd))
1977 return Op0;
1978 // Byte swap.
1979 if (MaskIdx == (0x0001020304050607ull | MaskUnd)) {
1980 SDValue T0 = DAG.getBitcast(MVT::i64, Op0);
1981 SDValue T1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::BSWAP, dl, MVT::i64, T0);
1982 return DAG.getBitcast(VecTy, T1);
1983 }
1984
1985 // Halfword picks.
1986 if (MaskIdx == (0x0d0c050409080100ull | MaskUnd))
1987 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_shuffeh, dl, VecTy, {Op1, Op0}, DAG);
1988 if (MaskIdx == (0x0f0e07060b0a0302ull | MaskUnd))
1989 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_shuffoh, dl, VecTy, {Op1, Op0}, DAG);
1990 if (MaskIdx == (0x0d0c090805040100ull | MaskUnd))
1991 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_vtrunewh, dl, VecTy, {Op1, Op0}, DAG);
1992 if (MaskIdx == (0x0f0e0b0a07060302ull | MaskUnd))
1993 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_vtrunowh, dl, VecTy, {Op1, Op0}, DAG);
1994 if (MaskIdx == (0x0706030205040100ull | MaskUnd)) {
1995 VectorPair P = opSplit(Op0, dl, DAG);
1996 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_packhl, dl, VecTy, {P.second, P.first}, DAG);
1997 }
1998
1999 // Byte packs.
2000 if (MaskIdx == (0x0e060c040a020800ull | MaskUnd))
2001 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_shuffeb, dl, VecTy, {Op1, Op0}, DAG);
2002 if (MaskIdx == (0x0f070d050b030901ull | MaskUnd))
2003 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_shuffob, dl, VecTy, {Op1, Op0}, DAG);
2004 }
2005
2006 return SDValue();
2007}

2009// Create a Hexagon-specific node for shifting a vector by an integer.
2010SDValue
2011HexagonTargetLowering::getVectorShiftByInt(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG)
2012 const {
2013 if (auto *BVN = dyn_cast<BuildVectorSDNode>(Op.getOperand(1).getNode())) {
2014 if (SDValue S = BVN->getSplatValue()) {
2015 unsigned NewOpc;
2016 switch (Op.getOpcode()) {
2017 case ISD::SHL:
2018 NewOpc = HexagonISD::VASL;
2019 break;
2020 case ISD::SRA:
2021 NewOpc = HexagonISD::VASR;
2022 break;
2023 case ISD::SRL:
2024 NewOpc = HexagonISD::VLSR;
2025 break;
2026 default:
2027 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected shift opcode");
2028 }
2029 return DAG.getNode(NewOpc, SDLoc(Op), ty(Op), Op.getOperand(0), S);
2030 }
2031 }
2032
2033 return SDValue();
2034}

2048SDValue
2049HexagonTargetLowering::LowerBITCAST(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2050 MVT ResTy = ty(Op);
2051 SDValue InpV = Op.getOperand(0);
2052 MVT InpTy = ty(InpV);
2053 assert(ResTy.getSizeInBits() == InpTy.getSizeInBits());
2054 const SDLoc &dl(Op);
2055
2056 // Handle conversion from i8 to v8i1.
2057 if (ResTy == MVT::v8i1) {
2058 SDValue Sc = DAG.getBitcast(tyScalar(InpTy), InpV);
2059 SDValue Ext = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Sc, dl, MVT::i32);
2060 return getInstr(Hexagon::C2_tfrrp, dl, ResTy, Ext, DAG);
2061 }
2062
2063 return SDValue();
2064}
2065
2066bool
2067HexagonTargetLowering::getBuildVectorConstInts(ArrayRef<SDValue> Values,
2068 MVT VecTy, SelectionDAG &DAG,
2069 MutableArrayRef<ConstantInt*> Consts) const {
2070 MVT ElemTy = VecTy.getVectorElementType();
2071 unsigned ElemWidth = ElemTy.getSizeInBits();
2072 IntegerType *IntTy = IntegerType::get(*DAG.getContext(), ElemWidth);
2073 bool AllConst = true;
2074
2075 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Values.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2076 SDValue V = Values[i];
2077 if (V.isUndef()) {
2078 Consts[i] = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, 0);
2079 continue;
2080 }
2081 // Make sure to always cast to IntTy.
2082 if (auto *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(V.getNode())) {
2083 const ConstantInt *CI = CN->getConstantIntValue();
2084 Consts[i] = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, CI->getValue().getSExtValue());
2085 } else if (auto *CN = dyn_cast<ConstantFPSDNode>(V.getNode())) {
2086 const ConstantFP *CF = CN->getConstantFPValue();
2087 APInt A = CF->getValueAPF().bitcastToAPInt();
2088 Consts[i] = ConstantInt::get(IntTy, A.getZExtValue());
2089 } else {
2090 AllConst = false;
2091 }
2092 }
2093 return AllConst;
2094}
2095
2096SDValue
2097HexagonTargetLowering::buildVector32(ArrayRef<SDValue> Elem, const SDLoc &dl,
2098 MVT VecTy, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2099 MVT ElemTy = VecTy.getVectorElementType();
2100 assert(VecTy.getVectorNumElements() == Elem.size());
2101
2102 SmallVector<ConstantInt*,4> Consts(Elem.size());
2103 bool AllConst = getBuildVectorConstInts(Elem, VecTy, DAG, Consts);
2104
2105 unsigned First, Num = Elem.size();
2106 for (First = 0; First != Num; ++First)
2107 if (!isUndef(Elem[First]))
2108 break;
2109 if (First == Num)
2110 return DAG.getUNDEF(VecTy);
2111
2112 if (AllConst &&
2113 llvm::all_of(Consts, [](ConstantInt *CI) { return CI->isZero(); }))
2114 return getZero(dl, VecTy, DAG);
2115
2116 if (ElemTy == MVT::i16) {
2117 assert(Elem.size() == 2);
2118 if (AllConst) {
2119 uint32_t V = (Consts[0]->getZExtValue() & 0xFFFF) |
2120 Consts[1]->getZExtValue() << 16;
2121 return DAG.getBitcast(MVT::v2i16, DAG.getConstant(V, dl, MVT::i32));
2122 }
2123 SDValue N = getInstr(Hexagon::A2_combine_ll, dl, MVT::i32,
2124 {Elem[1], Elem[0]}, DAG);
2125 return DAG.getBitcast(MVT::v2i16, N);
2126 }
2127
2128 if (ElemTy == MVT::i8) {
2129 // First try generating a constant.
2130 if (AllConst) {
2131 int32_t V = (Consts[0]->getZExtValue() & 0xFF) |
2132 (Consts[1]->getZExtValue() & 0xFF) << 8 |
2133 (Consts[1]->getZExtValue() & 0xFF) << 16 |
2134 Consts[2]->getZExtValue() << 24;
2135 return DAG.getBitcast(MVT::v4i8, DAG.getConstant(V, dl, MVT::i32));
2136 }
2137
2138 // Then try splat.
2139 bool IsSplat = true;
2140 for (unsigned i = 0; i != Num; ++i) {
2141 if (i == First)
2142 continue;
2143 if (Elem[i] == Elem[First] || isUndef(Elem[i]))
2144 continue;
2145 IsSplat = false;
2146 break;
2147 }
2148 if (IsSplat) {
2149 // Legalize the operand to VSPLAT.
2150 SDValue Ext = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Elem[First], dl, MVT::i32);
2151 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::VSPLAT, dl, VecTy, Ext);
2152 }
2153
2154 // Generate
2155 // (zxtb(Elem[0]) | (zxtb(Elem[1]) << 8)) |
2156 // (zxtb(Elem[2]) | (zxtb(Elem[3]) << 8)) << 16
2157 assert(Elem.size() == 4);
2158 SDValue Vs[4];
2159 for (unsigned i = 0; i != 4; ++i) {
2160 Vs[i] = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Elem[i], dl, MVT::i32);
2161 Vs[i] = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(Vs[i], dl, MVT::i8);
2162 }
2163 SDValue S8 = DAG.getConstant(8, dl, MVT::i32);
2164 SDValue T0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, MVT::i32, {Vs[1], S8});
2165 SDValue T1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SHL, dl, MVT::i32, {Vs[3], S8});
2166 SDValue B0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, MVT::i32, {Vs[0], T0});
2167 SDValue B1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, MVT::i32, {Vs[2], T1});
2168
2169 SDValue R = getInstr(Hexagon::A2_combine_ll, dl, MVT::i32, {B1, B0}, DAG);
2170 return DAG.getBitcast(MVT::v4i8, R);
2171 }
2172
2173#ifndef NDEBUG
2174 dbgs() << "VecTy: " << EVT(VecTy).getEVTString() << '\n';
2175#endif
2176 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected vector element type");
2177}
2178
2179SDValue
2180HexagonTargetLowering::buildVector64(ArrayRef<SDValue> Elem, const SDLoc &dl,
2181 MVT VecTy, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2182 MVT ElemTy = VecTy.getVectorElementType();
2183 assert(VecTy.getVectorNumElements() == Elem.size());
2184
2185 SmallVector<ConstantInt*,8> Consts(Elem.size());
2186 bool AllConst = getBuildVectorConstInts(Elem, VecTy, DAG, Consts);
2187
2188 unsigned First, Num = Elem.size();
2189 for (First = 0; First != Num; ++First)
2190 if (!isUndef(Elem[First]))
2191 break;
2192 if (First == Num)
2193 return DAG.getUNDEF(VecTy);
2194
2195 if (AllConst &&
2196 llvm::all_of(Consts, [](ConstantInt *CI) { return CI->isZero(); }))
2197 return getZero(dl, VecTy, DAG);
2198
2199 // First try splat if possible.
2200 if (ElemTy == MVT::i16) {
2201 bool IsSplat = true;
2202 for (unsigned i = 0; i != Num; ++i) {
2203 if (i == First)
2204 continue;
2205 if (Elem[i] == Elem[First] || isUndef(Elem[i]))
2206 continue;
2207 IsSplat = false;
2208 break;
2209 }
2210 if (IsSplat) {
2211 // Legalize the operand to VSPLAT.
2212 SDValue Ext = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(Elem[First], dl, MVT::i32);
2213 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::VSPLAT, dl, VecTy, Ext);
2214 }
2215 }
2216
2217 // Then try constant.
2218 if (AllConst) {
2219 uint64_t Val = 0;
2220 unsigned W = ElemTy.getSizeInBits();
2221 uint64_t Mask = (ElemTy == MVT::i8) ? 0xFFull
2222 : (ElemTy == MVT::i16) ? 0xFFFFull : 0xFFFFFFFFull;
2223 for (unsigned i = 0; i != Num; ++i)
2224 Val = (Val << W) | (Consts[Num-1-i]->getZExtValue() & Mask);
2225 SDValue V0 = DAG.getConstant(Val, dl, MVT::i64);
2226 return DAG.getBitcast(VecTy, V0);
2227 }
2228
2229 // Build two 32-bit vectors and concatenate.
2230 MVT HalfTy = MVT::getVectorVT(ElemTy, Num/2);
2231 SDValue L = (ElemTy == MVT::i32)
2232 ? Elem[0]
2233 : buildVector32(Elem.take_front(Num/2), dl, HalfTy, DAG);
2234 SDValue H = (ElemTy == MVT::i32)
2235 ? Elem[1]
2236 : buildVector32(Elem.drop_front(Num/2), dl, HalfTy, DAG);
2237 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::COMBINE, dl, VecTy, {H, L});
2238}

2240SDValue
2241HexagonTargetLowering::extractVector(SDValue VecV, SDValue IdxV,
2242 const SDLoc &dl, MVT ValTy, MVT ResTy,
2243 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2244 MVT VecTy = ty(VecV);
2245 assert(!ValTy.isVector() ||
2246 VecTy.getVectorElementType() == ValTy.getVectorElementType());
2247 unsigned VecWidth = VecTy.getSizeInBits();
2248 unsigned ValWidth = ValTy.getSizeInBits();
2249 unsigned ElemWidth = VecTy.getVectorElementType().getSizeInBits();
2250 assert((VecWidth % ElemWidth) == 0);
2251 auto *IdxN = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(IdxV);
2252
2253 // Special case for v{8,4,2}i1 (the only boolean vectors legal in Hexagon
2254 // without any coprocessors).
2255 if (ElemWidth == 1) {
2256 assert(VecWidth == VecTy.getVectorNumElements() && "Sanity failure");
2257 assert(VecWidth == 8 || VecWidth == 4 || VecWidth == 2);
2258 // Check if this is an extract of the lowest bit.
2259 if (IdxN) {
2260 // Extracting the lowest bit is a no-op, but it changes the type,
2261 // so it must be kept as an operation to avoid errors related to
2262 // type mismatches.
2263 if (IdxN->isNullValue() && ValTy.getSizeInBits() == 1)
2264 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::TYPECAST, dl, MVT::i1, VecV);
2265 }
2266
2267 // If the value extracted is a single bit, use tstbit.
2268 if (ValWidth == 1) {
2269 SDValue A0 = getInstr(Hexagon::C2_tfrpr, dl, MVT::i32, {VecV}, DAG);
2270 SDValue M0 = DAG.getConstant(8 / VecWidth, dl, MVT::i32);
2271 SDValue I0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, MVT::i32, IdxV, M0);
2272 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::TSTBIT, dl, MVT::i1, A0, I0);
2273 }
2274
2275 // Each bool vector (v2i1, v4i1, v8i1) always occupies 8 bits in
2276 // a predicate register. The elements of the vector are repeated
2277 // in the register (if necessary) so that the total number is 8.
2278 // The extracted subvector will need to be expanded in such a way.
2279 unsigned Scale = VecWidth / ValWidth;
2280
2281 // Generate (p2d VecV) >> 8*Idx to move the interesting bytes to
2282 // position 0.
2283 assert(ty(IdxV) == MVT::i32);
2284 unsigned VecRep = 8 / VecWidth;
2285 SDValue S0 = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, MVT::i32, IdxV,
2286 DAG.getConstant(8*VecRep, dl, MVT::i32));
2287 SDValue T0 = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::P2D, dl, MVT::i64, VecV);
2288 SDValue T1 = DAG.getNode(ISD::SRL, dl, MVT::i64, T0, S0);
2289 while (Scale > 1) {
2290 // The longest possible subvector is at most 32 bits, so it is always
2291 // contained in the low subregister.
2292 T1 = DAG.getTargetExtractSubreg(Hexagon::isub_lo, dl, MVT::i32, T1);
2293 T1 = expandPredicate(T1, dl, DAG);
2294 Scale /= 2;
2295 }
2296
2297 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::D2P, dl, ResTy, T1);
2298 }
2299
2300 assert(VecWidth == 32 || VecWidth == 64);
2301
2302 // Cast everything to scalar integer types.
2303 MVT ScalarTy = tyScalar(VecTy);
2304 VecV = DAG.getBitcast(ScalarTy, VecV);
2305
2306 SDValue WidthV = DAG.getConstant(ValWidth, dl, MVT::i32);
2307 SDValue ExtV;
2308
2309 if (IdxN) {
2310 unsigned Off = IdxN->getZExtValue() * ElemWidth;
2311 if (VecWidth == 64 && ValWidth == 32) {
2312 assert(Off == 0 || Off == 32);
2313 unsigned SubIdx = Off == 0 ? Hexagon::isub_lo : Hexagon::isub_hi;
2314 ExtV = DAG.getTargetExtractSubreg(SubIdx, dl, MVT::i32, VecV);
2315 } else if (Off == 0 && (ValWidth % 8) == 0) {
2316 ExtV = DAG.getZeroExtendInReg(VecV, dl, tyScalar(ValTy));
2317 } else {
2318 SDValue OffV = DAG.getConstant(Off, dl, MVT::i32);
2319 // The return type of EXTRACTU must be the same as the type of the
2320 // input vector.
2321 ExtV = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::EXTRACTU, dl, ScalarTy,
2322 {VecV, WidthV, OffV});
2323 }
2324 } else {
2325 if (ty(IdxV) != MVT::i32)
2326 IdxV = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(IdxV, dl, MVT::i32);
2327 SDValue OffV = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, MVT::i32, IdxV,
2328 DAG.getConstant(ElemWidth, dl, MVT::i32));
2329 ExtV = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::EXTRACTU, dl, ScalarTy,
2330 {VecV, WidthV, OffV});
2331 }
2332
2333 // Cast ExtV to the requested result type.
2334 ExtV = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(ExtV, dl, tyScalar(ResTy));
2335 ExtV = DAG.getBitcast(ResTy, ExtV);
2336 return ExtV;
2337}
2338
2339SDValue
2340HexagonTargetLowering::insertVector(SDValue VecV, SDValue ValV, SDValue IdxV,
2341 const SDLoc &dl, MVT ValTy,
2342 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2343 MVT VecTy = ty(VecV);
2344 if (VecTy.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1) {
2345 MVT ValTy = ty(ValV);
2346 assert(ValTy.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1);
2347 SDValue ValR = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::P2D, dl, MVT::i64, ValV);
2348 unsigned VecLen = VecTy.getVectorNumElements();
2349 unsigned Scale = VecLen / ValTy.getVectorNumElements();
2350 assert(Scale > 1);
2351
2352 for (unsigned R = Scale; R > 1; R /= 2) {
2353 ValR = contractPredicate(ValR, dl, DAG);
2354 ValR = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::COMBINE, dl, MVT::i64,
2355 DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::i32), ValR);
2356 }
2357 // The longest possible subvector is at most 32 bits, so it is always
2358 // contained in the low subregister.
2359 ValR = DAG.getTargetExtractSubreg(Hexagon::isub_lo, dl, MVT::i32, ValR);
2360
2361 unsigned ValBytes = 64 / Scale;
2362 SDValue Width = DAG.getConstant(ValBytes*8, dl, MVT::i32);
2363 SDValue Idx = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, MVT::i32, IdxV,
2364 DAG.getConstant(8, dl, MVT::i32));
2365 SDValue VecR = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::P2D, dl, MVT::i64, VecV);
2366 SDValue Ins = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::INSERT, dl, MVT::i32,
2367 {VecR, ValR, Width, Idx});
2368 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::D2P, dl, VecTy, Ins);
2369 }
2370
2371 unsigned VecWidth = VecTy.getSizeInBits();
2372 unsigned ValWidth = ValTy.getSizeInBits();
2373 assert(VecWidth == 32 || VecWidth == 64);
2374 assert((VecWidth % ValWidth) == 0);
2375
2376 // Cast everything to scalar integer types.
2377 MVT ScalarTy = MVT::getIntegerVT(VecWidth);
2378 // The actual type of ValV may be different than ValTy (which is related
2379 // to the vector type).
2380 unsigned VW = ty(ValV).getSizeInBits();
2381 ValV = DAG.getBitcast(MVT::getIntegerVT(VW), ValV);
2382 VecV = DAG.getBitcast(ScalarTy, VecV);
2383 if (VW != VecWidth)
2384 ValV = DAG.getAnyExtOrTrunc(ValV, dl, ScalarTy);
2385
2386 SDValue WidthV = DAG.getConstant(ValWidth, dl, MVT::i32);
2387 SDValue InsV;
2388
2389 if (ConstantSDNode *C = dyn_cast<ConstantSDNode>(IdxV)) {
2390 unsigned W = C->getZExtValue() * ValWidth;
2391 SDValue OffV = DAG.getConstant(W, dl, MVT::i32);
2392 InsV = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::INSERT, dl, ScalarTy,
2393 {VecV, ValV, WidthV, OffV});
2394 } else {
2395 if (ty(IdxV) != MVT::i32)
2396 IdxV = DAG.getZExtOrTrunc(IdxV, dl, MVT::i32);
2397 SDValue OffV = DAG.getNode(ISD::MUL, dl, MVT::i32, IdxV, WidthV);
2398 InsV = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::INSERT, dl, ScalarTy,
2399 {VecV, ValV, WidthV, OffV});
2400 }
2401
2402 return DAG.getNode(ISD::BITCAST, dl, VecTy, InsV);
2403}

2405SDValue
2406HexagonTargetLowering::expandPredicate(SDValue Vec32, const SDLoc &dl,
2407 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2408 assert(ty(Vec32).getSizeInBits() == 32);
2409 if (isUndef(Vec32))
2410 return DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::i64);
2411 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_vsxtbh, dl, MVT::i64, {Vec32}, DAG);
2412}

2414SDValue
2415HexagonTargetLowering::contractPredicate(SDValue Vec64, const SDLoc &dl,
2416 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2417 assert(ty(Vec64).getSizeInBits() == 64);
2418 if (isUndef(Vec64))
2419 return DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::i32);
2420 return getInstr(Hexagon::S2_vtrunehb, dl, MVT::i32, {Vec64}, DAG);

2423SDValue
2424HexagonTargetLowering::getZero(const SDLoc &dl, MVT Ty, SelectionDAG &DAG)
2425 const {
2426 if (Ty.isVector()) {
2427 assert(Ty.isInteger() && "Only integer vectors are supported here");
2428 unsigned W = Ty.getSizeInBits();
2429 if (W <= 64)
2430 return DAG.getBitcast(Ty, DAG.getConstant(0, dl, MVT::getIntegerVT(W)));
2431 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::VZERO, dl, Ty);
2432 }
2433
2434 if (Ty.isInteger())
2435 return DAG.getConstant(0, dl, Ty);
2436 if (Ty.isFloatingPoint())
2437 return DAG.getConstantFP(0.0, dl, Ty);
2438 llvm_unreachable("Invalid type for zero");
2439}

2441SDValue
2442HexagonTargetLowering::LowerBUILD_VECTOR(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2443 MVT VecTy = ty(Op);
2444 unsigned BW = VecTy.getSizeInBits();
2445 const SDLoc &dl(Op);
2446 SmallVector<SDValue,8> Ops;
2447 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Op.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i)
2448 Ops.push_back(Op.getOperand(i));
2449
2450 if (BW == 32)
2451 return buildVector32(Ops, dl, VecTy, DAG);
2452 if (BW == 64)
2453 return buildVector64(Ops, dl, VecTy, DAG);
2454
2455 if (VecTy == MVT::v8i1 || VecTy == MVT::v4i1 || VecTy == MVT::v2i1) {
2456 // For each i1 element in the resulting predicate register, put 1
2457 // shifted by the index of the element into a general-purpose register,
2458 // then or them together and transfer it back into a predicate register.
2459 SDValue Rs[8];
2460 SDValue Z = getZero(dl, MVT::i32, DAG);
2461 // Always produce 8 bits, repeat inputs if necessary.
2462 unsigned Rep = 8 / VecTy.getVectorNumElements();
2463 for (unsigned i = 0; i != 8; ++i) {
2464 SDValue S = DAG.getConstant(1ull << i, dl, MVT::i32);
2465 Rs[i] = DAG.getSelect(dl, MVT::i32, Ops[i/Rep], S, Z);
2466 }
2467 for (ArrayRef<SDValue> A(Rs); A.size() != 1; A = A.drop_back(A.size()/2)) {
2468 for (unsigned i = 0, e = A.size()/2; i != e; ++i)
2469 Rs[i] = DAG.getNode(ISD::OR, dl, MVT::i32, Rs[2*i], Rs[2*i+1]);
2470 }
2471 // Move the value directly to a predicate register.
2472 return getInstr(Hexagon::C2_tfrrp, dl, VecTy, {Rs[0]}, DAG);
2473 }
2474
2475 return SDValue();
2476}

2478SDValue
2479HexagonTargetLowering::LowerCONCAT_VECTORS(SDValue Op,
2480 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2481 MVT VecTy = ty(Op);
2482 const SDLoc &dl(Op);
2483 if (VecTy.getSizeInBits() == 64) {
2484 assert(Op.getNumOperands() == 2);
2485 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::COMBINE, dl, VecTy, Op.getOperand(1),
2486 Op.getOperand(0));
2487 }
2488
2489 MVT ElemTy = VecTy.getVectorElementType();
2490 if (ElemTy == MVT::i1) {
2491 assert(VecTy == MVT::v2i1 || VecTy == MVT::v4i1 || VecTy == MVT::v8i1);
2492 MVT OpTy = ty(Op.getOperand(0));
2493 // Scale is how many times the operands need to be contracted to match
2494 // the representation in the target register.
2495 unsigned Scale = VecTy.getVectorNumElements() / OpTy.getVectorNumElements();
2496 assert(Scale == Op.getNumOperands() && Scale > 1);
2497
2498 // First, convert all bool vectors to integers, then generate pairwise
2499 // inserts to form values of doubled length. Up until there are only
2500 // two values left to concatenate, all of these values will fit in a
2501 // 32-bit integer, so keep them as i32 to use 32-bit inserts.
2502 SmallVector<SDValue,4> Words[2];
2503 unsigned IdxW = 0;
2504
2505 for (SDValue P : Op.getNode()->op_values()) {
2506 SDValue W = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::P2D, dl, MVT::i64, P);
2507 for (unsigned R = Scale; R > 1; R /= 2) {
2508 W = contractPredicate(W, dl, DAG);
2509 W = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::COMBINE, dl, MVT::i64,
2510 DAG.getUNDEF(MVT::i32), W);
2511 }
2512 W = DAG.getTargetExtractSubreg(Hexagon::isub_lo, dl, MVT::i32, W);
2513 Words[IdxW].push_back(W);
2514 }
2515
2516 while (Scale > 2) {
2517 SDValue WidthV = DAG.getConstant(64 / Scale, dl, MVT::i32);
2518 Words[IdxW ^ 1].clear();
2519
2520 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Words[IdxW].size(); i != e; i += 2) {
2521 SDValue W0 = Words[IdxW][i], W1 = Words[IdxW][i+1];
2522 // Insert W1 into W0 right next to the significant bits of W0.
2523 SDValue T = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::INSERT, dl, MVT::i32,
2524 {W0, W1, WidthV, WidthV});
2525 Words[IdxW ^ 1].push_back(T);
2526 }
2527 IdxW ^= 1;
2528 Scale /= 2;
2529 }
2530
2531 // Another sanity check. At this point there should only be two words
2532 // left, and Scale should be 2.
2533 assert(Scale == 2 && Words[IdxW].size() == 2);
2534
2535 SDValue WW = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::COMBINE, dl, MVT::i64,
2536 Words[IdxW][1], Words[IdxW][0]);
2537 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::D2P, dl, VecTy, WW);
2538 }
2539
2540 return SDValue();
2541}

2573bool
2574HexagonTargetLowering::allowTruncateForTailCall(Type *Ty1, Type *Ty2) const {
2575 // Assuming the caller does not have either a signext or zeroext modifier, and
2576 // only one value is accepted, any reasonable truncation is allowed.
2577 if (!Ty1->isIntegerTy() || !Ty2->isIntegerTy())
2578 return false;
2579
2580 // FIXME: in principle up to 64-bit could be made safe, but it would be very
2581 // fragile at the moment: any support for multiple value returns would be
2582 // liable to disallow tail calls involving i64 -> iN truncation in many cases.
2583 return Ty1->getPrimitiveSizeInBits() <= 32;
2584}

2587HexagonTargetLowering::LowerLoad(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2588 LoadSDNode *LN = cast<LoadSDNode>(Op.getNode());
2589 unsigned ClaimAlign = LN->getAlignment();
2590 validateConstPtrAlignment(LN->getBasePtr(), SDLoc(Op), ClaimAlign);

2592 // don't need extra aligning.

2596SDValue
2597HexagonTargetLowering::LowerStore(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2598 StoreSDNode *SN = cast<StoreSDNode>(Op.getNode());
2599 unsigned ClaimAlign = SN->getAlignment();
2600 SDValue Ptr = SN->getBasePtr();
2601 const SDLoc &dl(Op);
2602 validateConstPtrAlignment(Ptr, dl, ClaimAlign);
2603
2604 MVT StoreTy = SN->getMemoryVT().getSimpleVT();
2605 unsigned NeedAlign = Subtarget.getTypeAlignment(StoreTy);
2606 if (ClaimAlign < NeedAlign)
2607 return expandUnalignedStore(SN, DAG);
2608 return Op;

2610
2611SDValue
2612HexagonTargetLowering::LowerUnalignedLoad(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG)
2613 const {
2614 LoadSDNode *LN = cast<LoadSDNode>(Op.getNode());
2615 MVT LoadTy = ty(Op);
2616 unsigned NeedAlign = Subtarget.getTypeAlignment(LoadTy);
2617 unsigned HaveAlign = LN->getAlignment();
2618 if (HaveAlign >= NeedAlign)
2619 return Op;
2620
2621 const SDLoc &dl(Op);
2622 const DataLayout &DL = DAG.getDataLayout();
2623 LLVMContext &Ctx = *DAG.getContext();
2624
2625 // If the load aligning is disabled or the load can be broken up into two
2626 // smaller legal loads, do the default (target-independent) expansion.
2627 bool DoDefault = false;
2628 // Handle it in the default way if this is an indexed load.
2629 if (!LN->isUnindexed())
2630 DoDefault = true;
2631
2632 if (!AlignLoads) {
2633 if (allowsMemoryAccess(Ctx, DL, LN->getMemoryVT(), *LN->getMemOperand()))
2634 return Op;
2635 DoDefault = true;
2636 }
2637 if (!DoDefault && (2 * HaveAlign) == NeedAlign) {
2638 // The PartTy is the equivalent of "getLoadableTypeOfSize(HaveAlign)".
2639 MVT PartTy = HaveAlign <= 8 ? MVT::getIntegerVT(8 * HaveAlign)
2640 : MVT::getVectorVT(MVT::i8, HaveAlign);
2641 DoDefault = allowsMemoryAccess(Ctx, DL, PartTy, *LN->getMemOperand());
2642 }
2643 if (DoDefault) {
2644 std::pair<SDValue, SDValue> P = expandUnalignedLoad(LN, DAG);
2645 return DAG.getMergeValues({P.first, P.second}, dl);
2646 }
2647
2648 // The code below generates two loads, both aligned as NeedAlign, and
2649 // with the distance of NeedAlign between them. For that to cover the
2650 // bits that need to be loaded (and without overlapping), the size of
2651 // the loads should be equal to NeedAlign. This is true for all loadable
2652 // types, but add an assertion in case something changes in the future.
2653 assert(LoadTy.getSizeInBits() == 8*NeedAlign);
2654
2655 unsigned LoadLen = NeedAlign;
2656 SDValue Base = LN->getBasePtr();
2657 SDValue Chain = LN->getChain();
2658 auto BO = getBaseAndOffset(Base);
2659 unsigned BaseOpc = BO.first.getOpcode();
2660 if (BaseOpc == HexagonISD::VALIGNADDR && BO.second % LoadLen == 0)
2661 return Op;
2662
2663 if (BO.second % LoadLen != 0) {
2664 BO.first = DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, MVT::i32, BO.first,
2665 DAG.getConstant(BO.second % LoadLen, dl, MVT::i32));
2666 BO.second -= BO.second % LoadLen;
2667 }
2668 SDValue BaseNoOff = (BaseOpc != HexagonISD::VALIGNADDR)
2669 ? DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::VALIGNADDR, dl, MVT::i32, BO.first,
2670 DAG.getConstant(NeedAlign, dl, MVT::i32))
2671 : BO.first;
2672 SDValue Base0 = DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(BaseNoOff, BO.second, dl);
2673 SDValue Base1 = DAG.getMemBasePlusOffset(BaseNoOff, BO.second+LoadLen, dl);
2674
2675 MachineMemOperand *WideMMO = nullptr;
2676 if (MachineMemOperand *MMO = LN->getMemOperand()) {
2677 MachineFunction &MF = DAG.getMachineFunction();
2678 WideMMO = MF.getMachineMemOperand(MMO->getPointerInfo(), MMO->getFlags(),
2679 2*LoadLen, LoadLen, MMO->getAAInfo(), MMO->getRanges(),
2680 MMO->getSyncScopeID(), MMO->getOrdering(),
2681 MMO->getFailureOrdering());
2682 }
2683
2684 SDValue Load0 = DAG.getLoad(LoadTy, dl, Chain, Base0, WideMMO);
2685 SDValue Load1 = DAG.getLoad(LoadTy, dl, Chain, Base1, WideMMO);
2686
2687 SDValue Aligned = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::VALIGN, dl, LoadTy,
2688 {Load1, Load0, BaseNoOff.getOperand(0)});
2689 SDValue NewChain = DAG.getNode(ISD::TokenFactor, dl, MVT::Other,
2690 Load0.getValue(1), Load1.getValue(1));
2691 SDValue M = DAG.getMergeValues({Aligned, NewChain}, dl);
2692 return M;
2693}
2694
2695SDValue
2696HexagonTargetLowering::LowerAddSubCarry(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2697 const SDLoc &dl(Op);
2698 unsigned Opc = Op.getOpcode();
2699 SDValue X = Op.getOperand(0), Y = Op.getOperand(1), C = Op.getOperand(2);
2700
2701 if (Opc == ISD::ADDCARRY)
2702 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::ADDC, dl, Op.getNode()->getVTList(),
2703 { X, Y, C });
2704
2705 EVT CarryTy = C.getValueType();
2706 SDValue SubC = DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::SUBC, dl, Op.getNode()->getVTList(),
2707 { X, Y, DAG.getLogicalNOT(dl, C, CarryTy) });
2708 SDValue Out[] = { SubC.getValue(0),
2709 DAG.getLogicalNOT(dl, SubC.getValue(1), CarryTy) };
2710 return DAG.getMergeValues(Out, dl);
2711}

2713SDValue
2714HexagonTargetLowering::LowerEH_RETURN(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2715 SDValue Chain = Op.getOperand(0);
2716 SDValue Offset = Op.getOperand(1);
2717 SDValue Handler = Op.getOperand(2);
2718 SDLoc dl(Op);
2719 auto PtrVT = getPointerTy(DAG.getDataLayout());
2720
2721 // Mark function as containing a call to EH_RETURN.
2722 HexagonMachineFunctionInfo *FuncInfo =
2723 DAG.getMachineFunction().getInfo<HexagonMachineFunctionInfo>();
2724 FuncInfo->setHasEHReturn();
2725
2726 unsigned OffsetReg = Hexagon::R28;
2727
2728 SDValue StoreAddr =
2729 DAG.getNode(ISD::ADD, dl, PtrVT, DAG.getRegister(Hexagon::R30, PtrVT),
2730 DAG.getIntPtrConstant(4, dl));
2731 Chain = DAG.getStore(Chain, dl, Handler, StoreAddr, MachinePointerInfo());
2732 Chain = DAG.getCopyToReg(Chain, dl, OffsetReg, Offset);
2733
2734 // Not needed we already use it as explict input to EH_RETURN.
2735 // MF.getRegInfo().addLiveOut(OffsetReg);
2736
2737 return DAG.getNode(HexagonISD::EH_RETURN, dl, MVT::Other, Chain);
2738}
