2740SDValue
2741HexagonTargetLowering::LowerOperation(SDValue Op, SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2742 unsigned Opc = Op.getOpcode();
2743
2744 // Handle INLINEASM first.
2745 if (Opc == ISD::INLINEASM || Opc == ISD::INLINEASM_BR)
2746 return LowerINLINEASM(Op, DAG);
2747
2748 if (isHvxOperation(Op)) {
2749 // If HVX lowering returns nothing, try the default lowering.
2750 if (SDValue V = LowerHvxOperation(Op, DAG))
2751 return V;
2752 }
2753
2754 switch (Opc) {
2755 default:
2756#ifndef NDEBUG
2757 Op.getNode()->dumpr(&DAG);
2758 if (Opc > HexagonISD::OP_BEGIN && Opc < HexagonISD::OP_END)
2759 errs() << "Error: check for a non-legal type in this operation\n";
2760#endif
2761 llvm_unreachable("Should not custom lower this!");
2762 case ISD::CONCAT_VECTORS: return LowerCONCAT_VECTORS(Op, DAG);
2763 case ISD::INSERT_SUBVECTOR: return LowerINSERT_SUBVECTOR(Op, DAG);
2764 case ISD::INSERT_VECTOR_ELT: return LowerINSERT_VECTOR_ELT(Op, DAG);
2765 case ISD::EXTRACT_SUBVECTOR: return LowerEXTRACT_SUBVECTOR(Op, DAG);
2766 case ISD::EXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT: return LowerEXTRACT_VECTOR_ELT(Op, DAG);
2767 case ISD::BUILD_VECTOR: return LowerBUILD_VECTOR(Op, DAG);
2768 case ISD::VECTOR_SHUFFLE: return LowerVECTOR_SHUFFLE(Op, DAG);
2769 case ISD::BITCAST: return LowerBITCAST(Op, DAG);
2770 case ISD::LOAD: return LowerLoad(Op, DAG);
2771 case ISD::STORE: return LowerStore(Op, DAG);
2772 case ISD::ADDCARRY:
2773 case ISD::SUBCARRY: return LowerAddSubCarry(Op, DAG);
2774 case ISD::SRA:
2775 case ISD::SHL:
2776 case ISD::SRL: return LowerVECTOR_SHIFT(Op, DAG);
2777 case ISD::ROTL: return LowerROTL(Op, DAG);
2778 case ISD::ConstantPool: return LowerConstantPool(Op, DAG);
2779 case ISD::JumpTable: return LowerJumpTable(Op, DAG);
2780 case ISD::EH_RETURN: return LowerEH_RETURN(Op, DAG);
2781 case ISD::RETURNADDR: return LowerRETURNADDR(Op, DAG);
2782 case ISD::FRAMEADDR: return LowerFRAMEADDR(Op, DAG);
2783 case ISD::GlobalTLSAddress: return LowerGlobalTLSAddress(Op, DAG);
2784 case ISD::ATOMIC_FENCE: return LowerATOMIC_FENCE(Op, DAG);
2785 case ISD::GlobalAddress: return LowerGLOBALADDRESS(Op, DAG);
2786 case ISD::BlockAddress: return LowerBlockAddress(Op, DAG);
2787 case ISD::GLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE: return LowerGLOBAL_OFFSET_TABLE(Op, DAG);
2788 case ISD::VASTART: return LowerVASTART(Op, DAG);
2789 case ISD::DYNAMIC_STACKALLOC: return LowerDYNAMIC_STACKALLOC(Op, DAG);
2790 case ISD::SETCC: return LowerSETCC(Op, DAG);
2791 case ISD::VSELECT: return LowerVSELECT(Op, DAG);
2792 case ISD::INTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN: return LowerINTRINSIC_WO_CHAIN(Op, DAG);
2793 case ISD::INTRINSIC_VOID: return LowerINTRINSIC_VOID(Op, DAG);
2794 case ISD::PREFETCH: return LowerPREFETCH(Op, DAG);
2795 case ISD::READCYCLECOUNTER: return LowerREADCYCLECOUNTER(Op, DAG);
2796 break;
2797 }
2798
2799 return SDValue();
2800}

2802void
2803HexagonTargetLowering::LowerOperationWrapper(SDNode *N,
2804 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results,
2805 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2806 // We are only custom-lowering stores to verify the alignment of the
2807 // address if it is a compile-time constant. Since a store can be modified
2808 // during type-legalization (the value being stored may need legalization),
2809 // return empty Results here to indicate that we don't really make any
2810 // changes in the custom lowering.
2811 if (N->getOpcode() != ISD::STORE)
2812 return TargetLowering::LowerOperationWrapper(N, Results, DAG);
2813}

2815void
2816HexagonTargetLowering::ReplaceNodeResults(SDNode *N,
2817 SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &Results,
2818 SelectionDAG &DAG) const {
2819 const SDLoc &dl(N);
2820 switch (N->getOpcode()) {
2821 case ISD::SRL:
2822 case ISD::SRA:
2823 case ISD::SHL:
2824 return;
2825 case ISD::BITCAST:
2826 // Handle a bitcast from v8i1 to i8.
2827 if (N->getValueType(0) == MVT::i8) {
2828 SDValue P = getInstr(Hexagon::C2_tfrpr, dl, MVT::i32,
2829 N->getOperand(0), DAG);
2830 Results.push_back(P);
2831 }
2832 break;
2833 }
2834}

2868std::pair<unsigned, const TargetRegisterClass*>
2869HexagonTargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(
2870 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, StringRef Constraint, MVT VT) const {
2871
2872 if (Constraint.size() == 1) {
2873 switch (Constraint[0]) {
2874 case 'r': // R0-R31
2875 switch (VT.SimpleTy) {
2876 default:
2877 return {0u, nullptr};
2878 case MVT::i1:
2879 case MVT::i8:
2880 case MVT::i16:
2881 case MVT::i32:
2882 case MVT::f32:
2883 return {0u, &Hexagon::IntRegsRegClass};
2884 case MVT::i64:
2885 case MVT::f64:
2886 return {0u, &Hexagon::DoubleRegsRegClass};
2887 }
2888 break;
2889 case 'a': // M0-M1
2890 if (VT != MVT::i32)
2891 return {0u, nullptr};
2892 return {0u, &Hexagon::ModRegsRegClass};
2893 case 'q': // q0-q3
2894 switch (VT.getSizeInBits()) {
2895 default:
2896 return {0u, nullptr};
2897 case 512:
2898 case 1024:
2899 return {0u, &Hexagon::HvxQRRegClass};
2900 }
2901 break;
2902 case 'v': // V0-V31
2903 switch (VT.getSizeInBits()) {
2904 default:
2905 return {0u, nullptr};
2906 case 512:
2907 return {0u, &Hexagon::HvxVRRegClass};
2908 case 1024:
2909 if (Subtarget.hasV60Ops() && Subtarget.useHVX128BOps())
2910 return {0u, &Hexagon::HvxVRRegClass};
2911 return {0u, &Hexagon::HvxWRRegClass};
2912 case 2048:
2913 return {0u, &Hexagon::HvxWRRegClass};
2914 }
2915 break;
2916 default:
2917 return {0u, nullptr};
2918 }
2919 }
2920
2921 return TargetLowering::getRegForInlineAsmConstraint(TRI, Constraint, VT);
2922}

2932/// isLegalAddressingMode - Return true if the addressing mode represented by
2933/// AM is legal for this target, for a load/store of the specified type.
2934bool HexagonTargetLowering::isLegalAddressingMode(const DataLayout &DL,
2935 const AddrMode &AM, Type *Ty,
2936 unsigned AS, Instruction *I) const {
2937 if (Ty->isSized()) {
2938 // When LSR detects uses of the same base address to access different
2939 // types (e.g. unions), it will assume a conservative type for these
2940 // uses:
2941 // LSR Use: Kind=Address of void in addrspace(4294967295), ...
2942 // The type Ty passed here would then be "void". Skip the alignment
2943 // checks, but do not return false right away, since that confuses
2944 // LSR into crashing.
2945 unsigned A = DL.getABITypeAlignment(Ty);
2946 // The base offset must be a multiple of the alignment.
2947 if ((AM.BaseOffs % A) != 0)
2948 return false;
2949 // The shifted offset must fit in 11 bits.
2950 if (!isInt<11>(AM.BaseOffs >> Log2_32(A)))
2951 return false;
2952 }
2953
2954 // No global is ever allowed as a base.
2955 if (AM.BaseGV)
2956 return false;
2957
2958 int Scale = AM.Scale;
2959 if (Scale < 0)
2960 Scale = -Scale;
2961 switch (Scale) {
2962 case 0: // No scale reg, "r+i", "r", or just "i".
2963 break;
2964 default: // No scaled addressing mode.
2965 return false;
2966 }
2967 return true;
2968}

2985/// IsEligibleForTailCallOptimization - Check whether the call is eligible
2986/// for tail call optimization. Targets which want to do tail call
2987/// optimization should implement this function.
2988bool HexagonTargetLowering::IsEligibleForTailCallOptimization(
2989 SDValue Callee,
2990 CallingConv::ID CalleeCC,
2991 bool IsVarArg,
2992 bool IsCalleeStructRet,
2993 bool IsCallerStructRet,
2994 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::OutputArg> &Outs,
2995 const SmallVectorImpl<SDValue> &OutVals,
2996 const SmallVectorImpl<ISD::InputArg> &Ins,
2997 SelectionDAG& DAG) const {
2998 const Function &CallerF = DAG.getMachineFunction().getFunction();
2999 CallingConv::ID CallerCC = CallerF.getCallingConv();
3000 bool CCMatch = CallerCC == CalleeCC;
3001
3002 // ***************************************************************************
3003 // Look for obvious safe cases to perform tail call optimization that do not
3004 // require ABI changes.
3005 // ***************************************************************************
3006
3007 // If this is a tail call via a function pointer, then don't do it!
3008 if (!isa<GlobalAddressSDNode>(Callee) &&
3009 !isa<ExternalSymbolSDNode>(Callee)) {
3010 return false;
3011 }
3012
3013 // Do not optimize if the calling conventions do not match and the conventions
3014 // used are not C or Fast.
3015 if (!CCMatch) {
3016 bool R = (CallerCC == CallingConv::C || CallerCC == CallingConv::Fast);
3017 bool E = (CalleeCC == CallingConv::C || CalleeCC == CallingConv::Fast);
3018 // If R & E, then ok.
3019 if (!R || !E)
3020 return false;
3021 }
3022
3023 // Do not tail call optimize vararg calls.
3024 if (IsVarArg)
3025 return false;
3026
3027 // Also avoid tail call optimization if either caller or callee uses struct
3028 // return semantics.
3029 if (IsCalleeStructRet || IsCallerStructRet)
3030 return false;
3031
3032 // In addition to the cases above, we also disable Tail Call Optimization if
3033 // the calling convention code that at least one outgoing argument needs to
3034 // go on the stack. We cannot check that here because at this point that
3035 // information is not available.
3036 return true;
3037}

3039/// Returns the target specific optimal type for load and store operations as
3040/// a result of memset, memcpy, and memmove lowering.
3041///
3042/// If DstAlign is zero that means it's safe to destination alignment can
3043/// satisfy any constraint. Similarly if SrcAlign is zero it means there isn't
3044/// a need to check it against alignment requirement, probably because the
3045/// source does not need to be loaded. If 'IsMemset' is true, that means it's
3046/// expanding a memset. If 'ZeroMemset' is true, that means it's a memset of
3047/// zero. 'MemcpyStrSrc' indicates whether the memcpy source is constant so it
3048/// does not need to be loaded. It returns EVT::Other if the type should be
3049/// determined using generic target-independent logic.
3050EVT HexagonTargetLowering::getOptimalMemOpType(uint64_t Size,
3051 unsigned DstAlign, unsigned SrcAlign, bool IsMemset, bool ZeroMemset,
3052 bool MemcpyStrSrc, const AttributeList &FuncAttributes) const {
3053
3054 auto Aligned = [](unsigned GivenA, unsigned MinA) -> bool {
3055 return (GivenA % MinA) == 0;
3056 };
3057
3058 if (Size >= 8 && Aligned(DstAlign, 8) && (IsMemset || Aligned(SrcAlign, 8)))
3059 return MVT::i64;
3060 if (Size >= 4 && Aligned(DstAlign, 4) && (IsMemset || Aligned(SrcAlign, 4)))
3061 return MVT::i32;
3062 if (Size >= 2 && Aligned(DstAlign, 2) && (IsMemset || Aligned(SrcAlign, 2)))
3063 return MVT::i16;
3064
3065 return MVT::Other;
3066}

3076std::pair<const TargetRegisterClass*, uint8_t>
3077HexagonTargetLowering::findRepresentativeClass(const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI,
3078 MVT VT) const {
3079 if (Subtarget.isHVXVectorType(VT, true)) {
3080 unsigned BitWidth = VT.getSizeInBits();
3081 unsigned VecWidth = Subtarget.getVectorLength() * 8;
3082
3083 if (VT.getVectorElementType() == MVT::i1)
3084 return std::make_pair(&Hexagon::HvxQRRegClass, 1);
3085 if (BitWidth == VecWidth)
3086 return std::make_pair(&Hexagon::HvxVRRegClass, 1);
3087 assert(BitWidth == 2 * VecWidth);
3088 return std::make_pair(&Hexagon::HvxWRRegClass, 1);
3089 }
3090
3091 return TargetLowering::findRepresentativeClass(TRI, VT);
3092}

3094bool HexagonTargetLowering::shouldReduceLoadWidth(SDNode *Load,
3095 ISD::LoadExtType ExtTy, EVT NewVT) const {
3096 // TODO: This may be worth removing. Check regression tests for diffs.
3097 if (!TargetLoweringBase::shouldReduceLoadWidth(Load, ExtTy, NewVT))
3098 return false;
3099
3100 auto *L = cast<LoadSDNode>(Load);
3101 std::pair<SDValue,int> BO = getBaseAndOffset(L->getBasePtr());
3102 // Small-data object, do not shrink.
3103 if (BO.first.getOpcode() == HexagonISD::CONST32_GP)
3104 return false;
3105 if (GlobalAddressSDNode *GA = dyn_cast<GlobalAddressSDNode>(BO.first)) {
3106 auto &HTM = static_cast<const HexagonTargetMachine&>(getTargetMachine());
3107 const auto *GO = dyn_cast_or_null<const GlobalObject>(GA->getGlobal());
3108 return !GO || !HTM.getObjFileLowering()->isGlobalInSmallSection(GO, HTM);
3109 }
3110 return true;
3111}

3113Value *HexagonTargetLowering::emitLoadLinked(IRBuilder<> &Builder, Value *Addr,
3114 AtomicOrdering Ord) const {
3115 BasicBlock *BB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3116 Module *M = BB->getParent()->getParent();
3117 auto PT = cast<PointerType>(Addr->getType());
3118 Type *Ty = PT->getElementType();
3119 unsigned SZ = Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
3120 assert((SZ == 32 || SZ == 64) && "Only 32/64-bit atomic loads supported");
3121 Intrinsic::ID IntID = (SZ == 32) ? Intrinsic::hexagon_L2_loadw_locked
3122 : Intrinsic::hexagon_L4_loadd_locked;
3123 Function *Fn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, IntID);
3124
3125 PointerType *NewPtrTy
3126 = Builder.getIntNTy(SZ)->getPointerTo(PT->getAddressSpace());
3127 Addr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Addr, NewPtrTy);
3128
3129 Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(Fn, Addr, "larx");
3130
3131 return Builder.CreateBitCast(Call, Ty);
3132}

3134/// Perform a store-conditional operation to Addr. Return the status of the
3135/// store. This should be 0 if the store succeeded, non-zero otherwise.
3136Value *HexagonTargetLowering::emitStoreConditional(IRBuilder<> &Builder,
3137 Value *Val, Value *Addr, AtomicOrdering Ord) const {
3138 BasicBlock *BB = Builder.GetInsertBlock();
3139 Module *M = BB->getParent()->getParent();
3140 Type *Ty = Val->getType();
3141 unsigned SZ = Ty->getPrimitiveSizeInBits();
3142
3143 Type *CastTy = Builder.getIntNTy(SZ);
3144 assert((SZ == 32 || SZ == 64) && "Only 32/64-bit atomic stores supported");
3145 Intrinsic::ID IntID = (SZ == 32) ? Intrinsic::hexagon_S2_storew_locked
3146 : Intrinsic::hexagon_S4_stored_locked;
3147 Function *Fn = Intrinsic::getDeclaration(M, IntID);
3148
3149 unsigned AS = Addr->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
3150 Addr = Builder.CreateBitCast(Addr, CastTy->getPointerTo(AS));
3151 Val = Builder.CreateBitCast(Val, CastTy);
3152
3153 Value *Call = Builder.CreateCall(Fn, {Addr, Val}, "stcx");
3154 Value *Cmp = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(Call, Builder.getInt32(0), "");
3155 Value *Ext = Builder.CreateZExt(Cmp, Type::getInt32Ty(M->getContext()));
3156 return Ext;
3157}
